<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.RegressController</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>true</client_callable><description/><name>RegressController</name><script><![CDATA[var RegressController = Class.create();
RegressController.prototype = {

    initialize: function() {

    },

    startExhaustiveTest: function() {
        var recordingStarted = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.startRecording(null, "exhaustive");
        var jsonParser = new JSON();
        var response = jsonParser.encode(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getSessionDetails());

        if (recordingStarted) {
            gs.addInfoMessage('⏺ Started Regress ATF Test Recorder. For best results, start by creating a new record.');
        }
		
        return response;
    },

    stopRecordingTest: function() {
        RegressATFRecordSessionv2.stopRecording();
        gs.addInfoMessage('⏹ Test Recording Stopped.');
        var testURL = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getATFTest().getLink();

        return testURL;
    },

    _process: function(formState) {
        //if i need to control for fromstate obj version in future
        if (formState.type == 'recordFormState_v1') {
            this.formState = formState;
            gs.debug(formState);
        }

        var grTest = this.createRegressionTest();

        return grTest;
    },

    createRegressionTest: function() {

        var grTest;

        try {
            var regress;

            var grExistingTest = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getATFTest();
            if (grExistingTest.isValidRecord()) {
                regress = new TestGenerator(this.formState, grExistingTest);
            } else {
                regress = new TestGenerator(this.formState);
            }

            regress.setupTest();

            grTest = regress.grTest;

        } catch (e) {
            gs.addErrorMessage(e);
        }

        return grTest;
    },


    type: 'RegressController'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-09-28 01:40:58</sys_created_on><sys_id>276fdb45db6f10109e10146139961998</sys_id><sys_mod_count>8</sys_mod_count><sys_name>RegressController</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_276fdb45db6f10109e10146139961998</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:28</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.VariableStateValidationTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>33f637e8c3ba220076173b0ac3d3aee1.</description><name>VariableStateValidationTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var VariableStateValidationTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
VariableStateValidationTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator, {

    generateTestStep: function() {
        var complexityLevel = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getRegressionLevel();

        this.setMandatoryCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingMandatoryVariables());
        this.setNotMandatoryCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotMandatoryVariables());
        this.setVisibleCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingVisibleVariables());
        this.setHiddenCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotVisibleVariables());
        this.setReadOnlyCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingReadonlyVariables());
        this.setNotReadOnlyCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotReadonlyVariables());

        if (complexityLevel != 'actions') {
            if (gs.nil(this.regressionObject.catalogItem)) {
                gs.debug('Validate Variable State Test Step not required.');
                //this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();
            } else {
                // Remmove all non variables, as some dodgy stuff gets picked up resulting in errors when replaying tests
				this.variableExclusionFilter = this.getVariableExclusionFilter();
                this.removeAllNonVariables();
                this.setFieldState(this.regressionObject.variableState);
                this.grATFStep.inputs.catalog_item = this.regressionObject.catalogItem;
                this.grATFStep.notes = 'The variable state of the form when a UI action is clicked during the recording.';
                AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
            }
        } else {
            this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();
        }
    },

    removeAllNonVariables: function() {
        var cleanedVisibleVariables = this.removeNonVariables(this.regressionObject.variableState.visible);
        this.regressionObject.variableState.visible = cleanedVisibleVariables;
		
        var cleanedHiddenVariables = this.removeNonVariables(this.regressionObject.variableState.hidden);
        this.regressionObject.variableState.hidden = cleanedHiddenVariables;
		
        var cleanedMandatoryVariables = this.removeNonVariables(this.regressionObject.variableState.mandatory);
        this.regressionObject.variableState.mandatory = cleanedMandatoryVariables;
		
        var cleanedOptionalVariables = this.removeNonVariables(this.regressionObject.variableState.optional);
        this.regressionObject.variableState.optional = cleanedOptionalVariables;
		
        var cleanedReadonlyVariables = this.removeNonVariables(this.regressionObject.variableState.readOnly);
		this.regressionObject.variableState.readOnly = cleanedReadonlyVariables;

        var cleanedEditableVariables = this.removeNonVariables(this.regressionObject.variableState.editable);
        this.regressionObject.variableState.editable = cleanedEditableVariables;
    },

    removeNonVariables: function(variableArray) {
        var arrayWithoutNonVariables = [];
        var grVariable = new GlideRecord('item_option_new');
        grVariable.addQuery('sys_id', 'IN', variableArray.toString());
		grVariable.addEncodedQuery(this.variableExclusionFilter);
        grVariable.query();
		var qry = grVariable.getEncodedQuery();
        while (grVariable.next()) {
            arrayWithoutNonVariables.push(grVariable.getUniqueValue());
        }

        return arrayWithoutNonVariables;
    },

	// Some variables don't detect field state properly in ATF
	getVariableExclusionFilter: function() {
		var encQry = 'typeNOT IN12,20,24,19,11,14,17,15^EQ';
		var grFilter = new GlideRecord('sys_filter');
		var filterSysId = gs.getProperty('regress.variable.capture.exclusion.filter');
		if ( grFilter.get(filterSysId) ) {
			encQry = grFilter.getValue('filter');
		}
		
		return encQry;
	},

    type: 'VariableStateValidationTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-01-06 11:47:49</sys_created_on><sys_id>adc33b6fdb8640109e10146139961922</sys_id><sys_mod_count>51</sys_mod_count><sys_name>VariableStateValidationTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_adc33b6fdb8640109e10146139961922</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:30</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_include_1cdaf3bcdb3333001c4af53a299619a2
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>false</active><api_name>global.CatalogueItemRegression</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Decided not to go down this path</description><name>CatalogueItemRegression</name><script><![CDATA[var CatalogueItemRegression = Class.create();
CatalogueItemRegression.prototype = Object.extendsObject(RegressionObject, {

	initialize: function(gr) {
		RegressionObject.prototype.initialize.call(this,gr);
		
		this.variableValues = this.getVariableValues(gr);
		this.catalogItem = gr.cat_item;
		
	},
	
	// Does not support multi row variable sets
	getVariableValues: function(gr) {
		var variableValues = "";
		var queries = [];
		var variables = gr.variables.getElements(); 
		
		for (var i=0;i<variables.length;i++) { 
			var question = variables[i].getQuestion(); 
			var query = gs.getMessage("IO:{0}={1}",[question.id, question.value]);
		    queries.push(query);
		} 

		variableValues = queries.join("^") + "^EQ";
		
		return variableValues;
	},
	
	getVariableUIPolicy:function() {

		// TODO
		// Get all policies for variable sets
		var builder = new CatalogUIPolicyBuilder();
		var grUIPolicies = this.getUIPoliciesForCatalogItem();
		builder.process(grUIPolicies);
		this.processUIPolicies(builder);
		// Check condition againt reg item
		// if onchange, only process if our reg variables are included
		// This should be possible by changing IO: to variables and checking against reg record using .checkRecord()
		// Add variables to field state arrays
		// To the opposite if reverse if false
		// Add logic for variable state field test step
		// variable is stored as sys_id of variable
		// Reference CatalogUIPolicyBuilder, GlideQueryString, UIPolicyBuilder, GlideFilter
		
	},
	
	getUIPoliciesForCatalogItem: function() {
		var gr = new GlideRecordSecure('catalog_ui_policy');
		gr.addActiveQuery();
		gr.addQuery('applies_to', 'item');
		gr.addQuery('catalog_item', this.catalogItem);
		gr.addQuery('applies_catalog', true);
		gr.orderBy('order');
		gr.query();	
	},
	
	processUIPolicies: function(builder) {
		
		for (var i = 0; i != builder.uiPolicy.fieldPolicies.length; i++) {
			var conditions = builder.uiPolicy.fieldPolicies[i].conditions;
			for (var j = 0; j != conditions.length; j++) {
				var condition = conditions[j];
				condition.type = "__preevaluated__";
				var f = new GlideFilter(condition.term, "UI Policy Filter");
				condition.value = f.match(gr, true);
				
			}
		}	
	},
	
	type: 'CatalogueItemRegression'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-09-08 02:54:03</sys_created_on><sys_id>1cdaf3bcdb3333001c4af53a299619a2</sys_id><sys_mod_count>13</sys_mod_count><sys_name>CatalogueItemRegression</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_1cdaf3bcdb3333001c4af53a299619a2</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:27</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.ValidateVariableValuesSPTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>2c8882759f1303002528d4b4232e708a</description><name>ValidateVariableValuesSPTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var ValidateVariableValuesSPTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
ValidateVariableValuesSPTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(SetVariableValuesTestStepGenerator, {

    initialize: function(grATFStep, regressionObject) {
        SetVariableValuesTestStepGenerator.prototype.initialize.call(this, grATFStep, regressionObject);
        this.regressionField = "validateVariableValues";
        this.inputStepField = "catalog_conditions";
    },
	
	setStepNotes: function() {
        this.grATFStep.notes = 'Check values of read-only Variables during the recording';

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description/><global>false</global><ignore_in_now_experience>false</ignore_in_now_experience><name>ServiceCatalogForm17</name><script><![CDATA[regress.ServiceCatalogForm17 = (function() {
    "use strict";

    function FormSnapshot(gForm) {
        regress.common.log('FormSnapshot()');

        if (typeof gForm == "undefined") {
            this.gForm = regress.common.gForm;
        } else {
            this.gForm = gForm;  
        }

        this.gUser = regress.common.gUser;
        this.variableStateChecker = new regress.VariableStateChecker.VariableStateChecker(gForm);

        this.recordFormState = {
            variableState: {},
            populatedVariableValues: '',
            validateVariableValues: '', 
            impersonate: this.gUser.userID,
            catalogItem: '',
            tableName: 'ni',
            type: 'recordFormState_v1'
        };

        this.recordFormState.catalogItem = this.gForm.getUniqueValue(); 
        this.recordFormState.impersonate = this.gUser.userID;
    };

    FormSnapshot.prototype.getGlideForm = function() {
        return this.gForm;
    };

    FormSnapshot.prototype.takeSnapshot = function() {
        regress.common.log('Taking Snapshot');
        this.recordFormState.variableState = this.snapshotVariableState();
        this.snapshotPopulatatedData();
        this.recordFormState.validateVariableValues = this.variableStateChecker.readOnlyAndPopulated.join("^");

        return this.recordFormState;
    },

    FormSnapshot.prototype.getSnapshotAsString = function() {
        var recordFormStateStr = JSON.stringify(this.recordFormState);
        return recordFormStateStr;
    },

    FormSnapshot.prototype.snapshotVariableState = function() {
        
        var allVariablesNameMap = this.gForm.nameMap;

        for (var f in allVariablesNameMap) {
            if (allVariablesNameMap.hasOwnProperty(f)) {
                var variableNameMap = allVariablesNameMap[f];
                var name = variableNameMap.prettyName;
                var reference = variableNameMap.questionID;
                this.variableStateChecker.getState(name, reference);
            }
        }

        return this.variableStateChecker.getAllStates();
    };


    FormSnapshot.prototype.addSnapshotToCurrentTest = function(isAsync) {
        var ga = this.getGlideAjaxSetup();
        //Using wait because server side test generation needs to occur before record is saved
        if (isAsync) {
            ga.getXML(this.generateTestResponse);
        } else {
            ga.getXMLWait();
            var answer = ga.getAnswer();
            this.generateTestResponse(answer);
            regress.common.log('Action:' + this.gForm.getActionName());
        }
        
        return true;
    }

    FormSnapshot.prototype.generateTestResponse = function(response) {
        if (response) {
            regress.common.gForm.addInfoMessage('Test steps for submitting a form have been added to the current Test.');
            return true;
        } else {
            return false;
        }

    }

    FormSnapshot.prototype.getGlideAjaxSetup = function() {
        var formStateJSON = JSON.stringify(this.recordFormState);
        var ga = new GlideAjax('TestGenAjax');
        ga.addParam('sysparm_name', 'process');
        ga.addParam('sysparm_form_state', formStateJSON);

        return ga;
    }

    FormSnapshot.prototype.snapshotPopulatatedData = function() {
        var populatedVariablesEncodedQuery = '';
        var serializedChangedVariables = this.gForm.serializeChanged(); // In CatalogForm this gets all variables, not just those that are changed
        var serializedChangedVariablesArray = serializedChangedVariables.split("&");
        var changedVariablesArray = [];

        for (var i = 0; i < serializedChangedVariablesArray.length; i++) {

            var serializedVariable = serializedChangedVariablesArray[i];
            if (serializedVariable.startsWith("IO:")) {
                var splitVar = serializedVariable.split("=");
                var variableID = splitVar[0];
                var value = splitVar[1];
                var variableName = this.gForm.getAppliedFieldName(variableID);
                var isEditable = this.gForm.isEditableField(
                    this.gForm.getSCUIElement(variableName),
                    this.gForm.getControl(variableName)
                );
                
                // We don't want to pick up variables with no value that are not visible or non-editable
                if (value != "" && value != null && value && isEditable) {
                    regress.common.log("Snapshot validate value for variable " + variableName + "=" + value);
                    changedVariablesArray.push(serializedVariable);                     
                } else {
                    regress.common.log("Ignoring variable " + variableName + " non editable or empty.");
                }

            }

        }

        populatedVariablesEncodedQuery = changedVariablesArray.join("^");
        regress.common.log("Variables changed: " + changedVariablesArray);
        regress.common.log("populatedVariablesEncodedQuery:" + populatedVariablesEncodedQuery);

        this.recordFormState.populatedVariableValues = populatedVariablesEncodedQuery;
        return populatedVariablesEncodedQuery;
    };

    return {
        FormSnapshot: FormSnapshot,
        type: 'ServiceCatalogForm17'
    };
    
})();]]></script><script_name/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-02-13 08:49:14</sys_created_on><sys_id>f0fc23ed2f5e6c105a445e492799b696</sys_id><sys_mod_count>46</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ServiceCatalogForm17</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_script_f0fc23ed2f5e6c105a445e492799b696</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-24 11:36:39</sys_updated_on><ui_type>10</ui_type><use_scoped_format>false</use_scoped_format></sys_ui_script></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="catalog_script_client"><catalog_script_client action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><applies_catalog>true</applies_catalog><applies_extended>false</applies_extended><applies_req_item>false</applies_req_item><applies_sc_task>false</applies_sc_task><applies_target_record>false</applies_target_record><applies_to>item</applies_to><cat_item display_value="Regress Properties">e194ce26db42c0109e10146139961954</cat_item><cat_variable>IO:613d13eadb86c0109e1014613996198d</cat_variable><condition/><description/><field/><global>true</global><isolate_script>true</isolate_script><messages/><name>Regress level capture options</name><order/><script><![CDATA[function onChange(control, oldValue, newValue, isLoading) {

    var regressLevel = newValue;

    switch (regressLevel) {
        case "actions":
            toggleSimpleOptions("false");
            toggleExhaustiveOptions("false");
			toggleActionsOnlyOptions("true");
            break;
        case "exhaustive":
            toggleExhaustiveOptions("true");
            toggleSimpleOptions("true");
			toggleActionsOnlyOptions("true");
            break;
        case "simple":
            toggleSimpleOptions("true");
            toggleExhaustiveOptions("false");
			toggleActionsOnlyOptions("false");
            break;
        default:
            //do nothing 
            break;

    }

    function toggleSimpleOptions(toggleValue) {
        g_form.setValue('not_visible', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('mandatory', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('read_only', toggleValue);
		g_form.setValue('var_not_visible', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('var_mandatory', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('var_read_only', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('ui_action_visible', toggleValue);
    }

    function toggleExhaustiveOptions(toggleValue) {
        g_form.setValue('validate_field_values_changed_by_scripts',toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('ui_action_not_visible', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('include_inactive_ui_actions', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('visible', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('not_mandatory', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('not_read_only', toggleValue);
		g_form.setValue('var_visible', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('var_not_mandatory', toggleValue);
        g_form.setValue('var_not_read_only', toggleValue);
    }
	
	function toggleActionsOnlyOptions(toggleValue) {
		g_form.setValue('record_outbound_emails', toggleValue);		
		g_form.setValue('notification_use_record_query', false);		
	}

}]]></script><sys_class_name>catalog_script_client</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-12-06 03:07:37</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>8439cf13db3c60509e1014613996190c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>17</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Regress level capture options</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>catalog_script_client_8439cf13db3c60509e1014613996190c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-16 12:20:41</sys_updated_on><table/><type>onChange</type><ui_type>0</ui_type><variable_set/><view/></catalog_script_client></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.RecordQueryTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>RecordQueryTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var RecordQueryTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
RecordQueryTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

    generateTestStep: function() {

        // Check if current record has a relationship to an existing record from this test so we can reference it
        // Returns an array of objects with properties 'field' and 'value';
        var potentialRecordReferences = this.getPotentialRecordReferences();
        var existingTestQryStepReferencesArray = this.findExistingTestStepReferences(potentialRecordReferences);

        if (existingTestQryStepReferencesArray.length > 0) {
            this.addExistingRecordReferenceToQuery(existingTestQryStepReferencesArray);

        } else if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.wasRecordingRecord(this.regressionObject.sysID)) {
            gs.debug('Removed Record Query step as Open Existing Record will open the previous record');
            this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();

        } else if (this.regressionObject.tableName == "sc_req_item" || this.regressionObject.tableName == "sc_request") {
            this.getReferenceFromOrderedCatalogueItem();
        } else if (this.regressionObject.tableName == "sys_email_log" ) {
            this.useRecordQueryForEmailTest();
        } else {
            this.useRecordQuery();
        }


    },



    getReferenceFromOrderedCatalogueItem: function() {
        var grOrderCatItemTestStep = this.getLastTestWithRequestOutput();
        if (grOrderCatItemTestStep.isValidRecord()) { // and it matches the cat item of the ritm?
            // how to match to request? Same cat item?
            var outputVariable = this.getStepOutputField(grOrderCatItemTestStep);
            var stepString = this.buildRecordIDString(grOrderCatItemTestStep.getUniqueValue(), outputVariable);
            if (this.regressionObject.tableName == "sc_req_item") {
                var ritmQry = "request=" + stepString;
                this.setContextualValueVariable('field_values', ritmQry);
                this.grATFStep.notes = 'Found Test Step reference to Request';
                TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
            } else if ( this.regressionObject.tableName == "sc_request") {
                // add test step marker for REQ
                RegressATFRecordSessionv2.addTestStepMarker(
                    this.regressionObject.sysID, 
                    this.regressionObject.tableName,
                    grOrderCatItemTestStep.getValue('sys_id')
                    );
                // delete this step, no longer needed
                // Open existing record will pickup this
                this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();
            }
        } else {
            this.useRecordQuery();
        }
    },

    getPotentialRecordReferences: function() {
        var potentialRecordReferences = [];
        var gr = new GlideRecord(this.regressionObject.tableName);

        if (gr.get(this.regressionObject.sysID)) {
            this.addExistingRecordQueryFieldsToQuery(gr);
            // Process all ref / doc id fields
            var geFields = gr.getFields();

            for (var i = 0; i < geFields.size(); i++) {
                var geField = geFields.get(i);
                var refTable = geField.getReferenceTable();
                var value = geField.getValue();
                var fieldName = geField.getName();
                if (!gs.nil(refTable) && !gs.nil(value)) {
                    potentialRecordReferences.push({
                        field: fieldName,
                        value: value
                    });
                }
            }
        }

        return potentialRecordReferences;
    },

    addExistingRecordQueryFieldsToQuery: function(gr) {
        var existingRecordQueryFields = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getExistingRecordQueryFields();
        var regressionQueryArray = [];
        for (i = 0; i < existingRecordQueryFields.length; i++) {
            var fieldName = existingRecordQueryFields[i];
            var fieldValue = gr.getValue(fieldName);
            if (fieldValue) {
                var qry = fieldName + "=" + fieldValue;
                regressionQueryArray.push(qry);
            }
        }
        if (regressionQueryArray.length > 0) {
            var newQuery = regressionQueryArray.join("^");
            if (!gs.nil(this.regressionObject.existingRecordQuery)) {
                newQuery = "^" + newQuery;
            }
            this.regressionObject.existingRecordQuery = this.regressionObject.existingRecordQuery + newQuery;
        }

        return regressionQueryArray;
    },

    addExistingRecordReferenceToQuery: function(existingTestQryStepReferencesArray) {
        var existingTestStepReferencesQry = existingTestQryStepReferencesArray.join("^");
        var existingRecordQuery = this.regressionObject.existingRecordQuery + "^" + existingTestStepReferencesQry;
		// Remove carriage returns, as they screw up the record query
		existingRecordQuery = existingRecordQuery.replaceAll("\r","");
        this.setContextualValueVariable('field_values', existingRecordQuery);
        if (this.regressionObject.type == "recordState_v1") {
            this.grATFStep.notes = 'Record snapshot taken of related record';
        } else {
            this.grATFStep.notes = 'Navigated to related record';
        }

        TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
    },



    findExistingTestStepReferences: function(potentialRecordReferences) {
        var existingRecordQueries = [];

        for (var i in potentialRecordReferences) {
            var refSysID = potentialRecordReferences[i].value;
            var fieldName = potentialRecordReferences[i].field;
            var marker = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.findTestStepMarker(refSysID);
            if (!gs.nil(marker.sys_id)) {
                // add it to existing
                var stepString = this.buildRecordIDString(marker.test_step, "record_id");
                existingRecordQueries.push(fieldName + "=" + stepString);
            }
        }

        return existingRecordQueries;
    },

    useRecordQueryForEmailTest: function() {
        var thirtySecondsAsDuration = "1970-01-01 00:00:30";
        this.grATFStep.setValue('timeout',thirtySecondsAsDuration); 
        this.grATFStep.inputs['table'] = this.regressionObject.tableName;
        this.grATFStep.notes = "Email with subject '" + this.regressionObject.display + "' that was sent during the recording. Record Query should be used until existing issues (KB0863789) are fixed with Test Step 'Validate Outbound Email Triggered from Notification'. You can enable this behaviour in Properties if desired.";
        
        // When variable contains any references to test steps, this method must be used
        this.setContextualValueVariable('field_values',this.regressionObject.existingRecordQuery);
        this.grATFStep.inputs['field_values'] = this.regressionObject.existingRecordQuery;
        TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);      
        //force an update after?
    },

    useRecordQuery: function() {
		
        this.grATFStep.inputs['field_values'] = this.regressionObject.existingRecordQuery;
        this.grATFStep.notes = 'Find a record similar to ' + this.regressionObject.tableName + ' ' + this.regressionObject.display;
        TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
    },


    type: 'RecordQueryTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-07-18 08:31:33</sys_created_on><sys_id>1165d954db3233001c4af53a2996197d</sys_id><sys_mod_count>75</sys_mod_count><sys_name>RecordQueryTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_1165d954db3233001c4af53a2996197d</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:32</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>false</active><api_name>global.RegressionObject</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>RegressionObject</name><script><![CDATA[var RegressionObject = Class.create();

RegressionObject.GetWorker = function(regressionObject) {
	var regressionWorker;
	
	switch(regressionObject.getTableName()) {
		case "sys_ui_policy":
			regressionWorker = new UIPolicyRegression(regressionObject);
			break;
		case "sc_req_item":
			regressionWorker = new CatalogueItemRegression(regressionObject);
			break;
		default:
		regressionWorker = new RegressionObject(regressionObject);
		
	}
	
	return regressionWorker;
	
};

RegressionObject.prototype = {
	initialize: function(regressionObject) {
		this.regressionObject = regressionObject;
		
		this.mandatoryFields = '';
		this.notMandatoryFields = '';
		this.visibleFields ='';
		this.notVisibleFields ='';
		this.readOnlyFields = '';
		this.notReadOnlyFields = '';
		this.visibleUIActions = '';
		
		this.tableName = regressionObject.getTableName();
		this.sys_id = regressionObject.getValue('sys_id');
		this.impersonate = gs.getUserID();
		this.viewName = '';
		this.conditions = regressionObject.getEncodedQuery();
		this.setFieldValues = [];
		
	},
	
	setAction: function(uiActionSysID) {
		this.uiActionSysID = uiActionSysID;
	},

	
	type: 'RegressionObject'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-07-24 08:52:38</sys_created_on><sys_id>69b3505adb3233001c4af53a299619a0</sys_id><sys_mod_count>17</sys_mod_count><sys_name>RegressionObject</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_69b3505adb3233001c4af53a299619a0</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:29</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.OutboundEmailTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL_GENERATED_BY_NOTIFICATION</description><name>OutboundEmailTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var OutboundEmailTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
OutboundEmailTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {
	
	generateTestStep: function() {

		var isEmailCaptureEnabled = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotifications();

		if (isEmailCaptureEnabled) {
			// Give plenty of time to find emails, they can take a while to send
			var thirtySecondsAsDuration = "1970-01-01 00:00:30";
			this.grATFStep.setValue('timeout',thirtySecondsAsDuration); 
			if (!gs.nil(this.regressionObject.sourceSysID)) {
				this.grATFStep.inputs[this.regressionObject.sourceField] = this.regressionObject.sourceSysID;
			}

			var testStepRecordReference = this.buildRecordIDString(this.regressionObject.testStepId, "record_id");
			var testStepTableReference = this.buildRecordIDString(this.regressionObject.testStepId, "table");
			var instanceCondition = "instance=" + testStepRecordReference;
			var tableCondition = "target_table=" + testStepTableReference;
			var typeCondition = "typeINsend-ignored,send-ready,sent";
			var recipientsCondition = "recipients=" + this.regressionObject.recipients;

			var conditionsArray = [instanceCondition,tableCondition,typeCondition,recipientsCondition];
			var encQry = conditionsArray.join("^") + "^EQ";

			this.grATFStep.notes = "Email with subject '" + this.regressionObject.subject + "' that was sent during the recording.";
			
			this.setContextualValueVariable('conditions',encQry);
			this.grATFStep.inputs['conditions'] = encQry;
			TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
		}
	},

    type: 'OutboundEmailTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-03-03 10:50:46</sys_created_on><sys_id>ed55f4a72faee4105a445e492799b692</sys_id><sys_mod_count>39</sys_mod_count><sys_name>OutboundEmailTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_ed55f4a72faee4105a445e492799b692</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:27</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Takes a snapshot of the forms current state.</description><global>false</global><ignore_in_now_experience>false</ignore_in_now_experience><name>ServiceCatalogFormSP</name><script><![CDATA[regress.ServiceCatalogFormSP = (function() {
    "use strict";
    
    SPFormSnapShot.prototype = Object.create(regress.ServiceCatalogForm17.FormSnapshot.prototype);
    SPFormSnapShot.constructor = SPFormSnapShot;

    function SPFormSnapShot(gForm, isOrderGuide) {
        regress.ServiceCatalogForm17.FormSnapshot.call(this,gForm);

        if (typeof isOrderGuide == "undefined") {
            isOrderGuide = false;
        }
        this.recordFormState.tableName = ""; // Use SP template
        this.variableStateChecker = new regress.SPVariableStateChecker.SPVariableStateChecker(gForm);
        this.recordFormState.multiRowVariableSetsState = {};
        this.multiRowVariableSets = {};
        this.recordFormState.servicePortal = this.getServicePortalURLSuffix();  
        this.recordFormState.partOfOrderGuide =  isOrderGuide;

    };



    SPFormSnapShot.prototype.takeSnapShot =  function() {
        regress.ServiceCatalogForm17.FormSnapshot.prototype.takeSnapshot.call(this);
        this.recordFormState.multiRowVariableSetsState = this.multiRowVariableSets;
        console.log(this.recordFormState);
    };

    SPFormSnapShot.prototype.snapshotVariableState = function() {
        var allVariables = this.gForm.getFieldNames();

        for (var v in allVariables) {

            if (allVariables.hasOwnProperty(v)) {
                var variableName = allVariables[v];
                var variableSysId = this.gForm.getField(variableName).sys_id;
                this.variableStateChecker.getState(variableName,variableSysId);
            }
        }
        return this.variableStateChecker.getAllStates();
    };


    SPFormSnapShot.prototype.addSnapshotToCurrentTest = function() {
        var showMsg =  !this.recordFormState.partOfOrderGuide;
        regress.ServiceCatalogForm17.FormSnapshot.prototype.addSnapshotToCurrentTest.call(this,true,showMsg); // async ga call
    };

    SPFormSnapShot.prototype.getServicePortalURLSuffix = function() {
        var answer='';
        var pattern = /\.service-now.com\/(.+)\?/g;
        try {
            var matches = new RegExp(pattern).exec(top.window.location.href);
            if (matches.length >= 2) {
                answer = matches[1];
            }
        } catch (e) {
            regress.common.log('Could not find URL from window');
        }

        return answer;
    };

    SPFormSnapShot.prototype.snapshotPopulatatedData = function() {

        var changedFieldsOnly = true;
        var serializedForm = this.gForm.serialize(changedFieldsOnly);
        var changedVariables = [];
        if (serializedForm) {
            for (var v = 0; v < serializedForm.length; v++ ) {
                var serializedVariable = serializedForm[v];
                if (this.gForm.isEditableField(serializedVariable.name)) {
                    if (serializedVariable.type == "sc_multi_row") {
                        regress.common.log('found MRVS')
                        this.snapshotChangedVariableSetValues(serializedVariable);
                    } else {
                        changedVariables.push(serializedVariable.catalogFieldName + "=" +this.gForm.getValue(serializedVariable.name) );
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        this.recordFormState.populatedVariableValues = changedVariables.join("^");
    };

    SPFormSnapShot.prototype.snapshotChangedVariableSetValues = function(serializedVariableSet) {
        var sys_id = "IO:" + serializedVariableSet.id;
        var changedVariableSetValues = this.parseVariableSetChangedValues(serializedVariableSet);
        this.multiRowVariableSets[sys_id] = changedVariableSetValues;
    };

    SPFormSnapShot.prototype.parseVariableSetChangedValues = function(variableSet) {  
        var value = this.gForm.getValue(variableSet.name);
        var changedVariables = [];
        var rows = JSON.parse(value);
        for (var r = 0; r < rows.length; r++ ) {
            var row = [];
            var varObj = Object.keys(rows[r]);
            for (var i in varObj) {
                // ATF Test Step for variables expects format NI:SYS_ID, but we only have label
                // No OOTB API in SP GFORM to determine NI from Label, so we have to do it ourselves
                var ioValue = this.getMRVSVariableIOValue(variableSet, varObj[i]);
                if (ioValue != "") {
                    row.push(ioValue + "=" + rows[r][varObj[i]] );
                } else {
                    log('Could not find NI Value for ' + varObj[i]);
                }
            }
            changedVariables.push(row.join("^"));
        }
        
        return changedVariables;
    };
    
    SPFormSnapShot.prototype.getMRVSVariableIOValue = function(variableSet, variableLabel) {
        if (!variableSet.hasOwnProperty('columns_meta')) {
            log('MRVS no longer has property columns_meta, cannot determine IOValue in getMRVSVariableNIValue()');
            return; 
        }
        
        var l = variableSet.columns_meta.length;
        
        for(var i = 0; i< l; i++) {
            var metaRow = variableSet.columns_meta[i];
            if (metaRow.name == variableLabel) {
                var ioValue = "IO:" + metaRow.id;
                return ioValue;
            }
        }
    };
 
    return {
        SPFormSnapShot : SPFormSnapShot,
        type: 'ServiceCatalogFormSP'
    }

})();

]]></script><script_name/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-12-08 02:09:30</sys_created_on><sys_id>c7391cd6db210010f0a2f282399619f0</sys_id><sys_mod_count>349</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ServiceCatalogFormSP</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_script_c7391cd6db210010f0a2f282399619f0</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:23</sys_updated_on><ui_type>10</ui_type><use_scoped_format>false</use_scoped_format></sys_ui_script></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_processor"><sys_processor action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><class_name/><description/><interactive>false</interactive><name>Start Recording Regression Test</name><parameters/><params_endpoint/><path>startRecordingRegressionATFTest</path><path_endpoint/><require_csrf>false</require_csrf><roles>snc_internal</roles><script><![CDATA[(function process(g_request, g_response, g_processor) {
	var response = "";

	 if (!RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRecording()) {
		var recordingStarted = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.startRecording();
		var jsonParser = new JSON();
		response = jsonParser.encode(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getSessionDetails());
		g_response.sendRedirect(gs.getSession().getStack().pop());
		if (recordingStarted) {
			gs.addInfoMessage('⏺ Started Regress ATF Test Recorder. For best results, start by creating a new record.');
		}
	 } 


	
})(g_request, g_response, g_processor);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_processor</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-01-02 07:34:34</sys_created_on><sys_id>9563125adb4680109e1014613996191c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>20</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Start Recording Regression Test</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_processor_9563125adb4680109e1014613996191c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:25</sys_updated_on><type>script</type><xframe_sameorigin>false</xframe_sameorigin></sys_processor></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_fix"><sys_script_fix action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><before>false</before><description>Installs additional options for recording at the field level.</description><name>ContextMenuInstaller</name><record_for_rollback>true</record_for_rollback><script><![CDATA[//Where in the UI Macro to inster this
var find_string = '<j:if test="${jvar_personalize_dictionary == true }" >';

//Functionality for Regress
var uimacro = '<g:macro_invoke macro="regress_context_menu" />';
var replace_string = '\n    // Regress Customisation to add ATF field context menu options\n    ' + uimacro + '\n\n    <j:if test="${jvar_personalize_dictionary == true }" >\n';

//Retrieve the UI Macro
var ui_macro = new GlideRecord('sys_ui_macro');
ui_macro.get('name', 'element_context');

var macro_xml = ui_macro.getValue('xml');


var hasRegressUIMacroCode = macro_xml.indexOf(uimacro) == -1 ;
if (hasRegressUIMacroCode) {
    var new_xml = macro_xml.replace(find_string, replace_string); //add functionality on line 100 (As of Utah, OOB)
    ui_macro.setValue('xml', new_xml);
    ui_macro.update();
}]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_fix</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sn-nerd</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2023-02-17 11:01:51</sys_created_on><sys_id>511a484a47812150cef68a5f746d43b8</sys_id><sys_mod_count>12</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ContextMenuInstaller</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_fix_511a484a47812150cef68a5f746d43b8</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-17 12:02:18</sys_updated_on><unloadable>false</unloadable></sys_script_fix></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>false</active><api_name>global.PolicyActionToFieldStateStepProcessor</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>PolicyActionToFieldStateStepProcessor</name><script><![CDATA[var PolicyActionToFieldStateStepProcessor = Class.create();
PolicyActionToFieldStateStepProcessor.prototype = {
	
    initialize: function( fieldState ) {
		this.isFieldState = [];
		this.isNotFieldState = [];
		
		this.fieldState = fieldState;
    },
	
	processPolicyAction: function(grUIPolicyAction) {
		var fieldName = grUIPolicyAction.getValue('field');
			
		var mandatoryValue = grUIPolicyAction.getValue(this.fieldState);
			
		switch(mandatoryValue) {
			case "true" : this.isFieldState.push(fieldName); break;
			case "false" : this.isNotFieldState.push(fieldName); break;
			case "ignore" : break;	
			default:
		}
		
	},
	
	getIsFieldState: function() {
		return this.isFieldState.join(",");
	},
	
	getIsNotFieldState: function() {
		return this.isNotFieldState.join(",");
	},

    type: 'PolicyActionToFieldStateStepProcessor'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-06-27 08:40:32</sys_created_on><sys_id>456dc1e5db5233001c4af53a2996192e</sys_id><sys_mod_count>11</sys_mod_count><sys_name>PolicyActionToFieldStateStepProcessor</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_456dc1e5db5233001c4af53a2996192e</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:28</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.TestGenAjax</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>true</client_callable><description/><name>TestGenAjax</name><script><![CDATA[var TestGenAjax = Class.create();
TestGenAjax.prototype = Object.extendsObject(global.AbstractAjaxProcessor, {

    process: function() {
        var formStateString = this.getParameter('sysparm_form_state').toString();
        var formState = JSON.parse(formStateString);
        var isRecording = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRecording();
        var url;
        if (isRecording) {
            var grTest = this._process(formState);
            url = grTest.getLink();
        } else {
            throw('Regress is not recording');
        }

        return url;
    },

	_mockFormLoadAjaxCall: function() {

		
	},
	
    _process: function(formState) {
        //if i need to control for fromstate obj version in future
        if (formState.type == 'recordFormState_v1') {
            this.formState = formState;
            gs.debug(formState);
        }

        var grTest = this.createRegressionTest();
		
        return grTest;
    },


    createRegressionTest: function() {

        var grTest;

        try {
            var regress;

            var grExistingTest = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getATFTest();
            if (grExistingTest.isValidRecord()) {
                regress = new TestGenerator(this.formState, grExistingTest);
            } else {
                regress = new TestGenerator(this.formState);
            }

            regress.setupTest();

            grTest = regress.grTest;

        } catch (e) {
            gs.addErrorMessage(e);
        }

        return grTest;
    },



    type: 'TestGenAjax'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-07-24 08:37:08</sys_created_on><sys_id>ce201896db3233001c4af53a299619ee</sys_id><sys_mod_count>177</sys_mod_count><sys_name>TestGenAjax</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_ce201896db3233001c4af53a299619ee</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:31</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.SetValuesTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>SetValuesTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var SetValuesTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
SetValuesTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {
	
	generateTestStep: function() {
        this.isFirst = true;
		if (gs.nil(this.regressionObject[this.regressionField])) {
            this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();
        } else {
            var fieldValues = this.regressionObject[this.regressionField].toString();
            if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCreateUserWhenImpersonating()) {
                fieldValues = this.replaceCurrentUserSysIDWithStepRef(fieldValues);
            } 
            this.fieldValues = fieldValues;
            this.generateStepsForValues(this.fieldValues);
        }	
	},
	
    generateStepsForValues: function(fieldValues) {
        // SN can struggle when too many fields are set at once
        // Split each set values step into no more then N fields
        gs.info('SetValuesTestStepGenerator generateStepsForValues');
        var fields = fieldValues.split('^');
        var maxChunkSize = parseInt(gs.getProperty('regress.setfields.chunksize',8));
        var fieldCount = fields.length;
        var iterations = Math.floor(fieldCount / maxChunkSize);
        var hasRemainder = fieldCount % maxChunkSize > 0;
        if (hasRemainder) {
            iterations++;
        }

        for (var i =1; i <= iterations;i++) {
            var segment = iterations + 1- i;
            var stepNote = 'The fields populated by the user during recording. (' + (segment) + ' of ' + iterations + ')';
            gs.info(stepNote);
            var subsetFields = fields.splice(-maxChunkSize,maxChunkSize); // In reverse order (start at end of array), so each new step comes ahead of the last
            gs.info('Chunk:' + subsetFields.toString());
            this.generateSetValuesTestStep(subsetFields.join("^"), stepNote);
        } 
    },

    generateSetValuesTestStep: function(fieldValues, notes) {
        gs.info('SetValuesTestStepGenerator generateSetValuesTestStep ' + this.inputStepField);
        this.grATFStep.notes = notes;
        this.grATFStep.inputs[this.inputStepField] = fieldValues;

        // only insert (copy) if this is a second setfields from chunking or depedent fields
        if (this.isFirst == false) {
            this.grATFStep.insert();
            this.setContextualValueVariable(this.inputStepField,fieldValues);
        } 

        if (this.isFirst == true) {
            this.setContextualValueVariable(this.inputStepField,fieldValues);
            this.isFirst = false;
            this.grATFStep.update();
        } 
    },
	
    type: 'SetValuesTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>snnerd</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2022-05-02 09:27:26</sys_created_on><sys_id>1b3e45542f5301109d5b5d8b2799b697</sys_id><sys_mod_count>31</sys_mod_count><sys_name>SetValuesTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_1b3e45542f5301109d5b5d8b2799b697</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-24 12:40:13</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description/><global>false</global><ignore_in_now_experience>false</ignore_in_now_experience><name>FieldStateChecker</name><script><![CDATA[var regress = regress || {};

regress.FieldStateChecker = (function() {



    function FieldStateChecker() {
        regress.VariableStateChecker.VariableStateChecker.call(this);

    }

    //Inherit from VariableStateChecker
    FieldStateChecker.prototype = Object.create(regress.VariableStateChecker.VariableStateChecker.prototype);
    FieldStateChecker.constructor = FieldStateChecker;

    FieldStateChecker.prototype.getControl = function(field) {
        var control = this.gForm.getControl(field);

        return control;
    };

    FieldStateChecker.prototype.determineState = function(assertType,field,fieldGE,control ) {
        var actualValue;

        if ("mandatory" == assertType)
            actualValue = !!this.gForm.isMandatory(field);
        else if ("read only" == assertType)
            actualValue = (!fieldGE) ? false : !!this.gForm.isReadOnly(fieldGE, control);
        else if ("visible" == assertType)
            actualValue = (!fieldGE) ? false : !!this.gForm.isVisible(fieldGE, control);

        return actualValue;
    };

    return {
        FieldStateChecker: FieldStateChecker,
        type: 'FieldStateChecker'
    };

})();]]></script><script_name/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-02-13 11:55:57</sys_created_on><sys_id>ebe79cb52f12ac105a445e492799b680</sys_id><sys_mod_count>7</sys_mod_count><sys_name>FieldStateChecker</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_script_ebe79cb52f12ac105a445e492799b680</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:23</sys_updated_on><ui_type>10</ui_type><use_scoped_format>false</use_scoped_format></sys_ui_script></record_update>

A Test is of little value until it has been shown to Pass.

Execute the Test that was generated to validate that all pertinant details were recorded as expected.

In some circumstances the Test may not pass and manual adjustment is required. Reasons include:

  • User input not detected/supported by Regress
  • Too many fields populated at one time resulting in Client Scripts / UI Policies not running
  • Form interceptors used to create new records

Please raise any defects on the Regress Patreon.

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.SetVariableValuesTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>SetVariableValuesTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var SetVariableValuesTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
SetVariableValuesTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(SetValuesTestStepGenerator, {

    initialize: function(grATFStep, regressionObject) {
        SetValuesTestStepGenerator.prototype.initialize.call(this, grATFStep, regressionObject);
        this.regressionField = "populatedVariableValues";
        this.inputStepField = "variable_values";
    },

    generateTestStep: function() {

        if (!gs.nil(this.regressionObject.catalogItem)) {
            this.grATFStep.inputs['catalog_item'] = this.regressionObject.catalogItem;
        }

        SetValuesTestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
    },

    replaceRefValuesWithStepReferences: function(table, queryString) {
        var newQueryString = queryString;

        var gQueryString = new GlideQueryString(table, queryString);
        gQueryString.deserialize();
        var terms = gQueryString.getTerms();
        for (var i = 0; i < terms.size(); i++) {
            var term = terms.get(i);
            var value = term.getValue();
            // term.setValue() throws exception, can't use, must replace in full string
            
            var sysIDRegEx = /[0-9a-f]{32}/;
            if (value.match(sysIDRegEx)) {
                var testMarker = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.findTestStepMarker(value);
                var testStep = testMarker.test_step;
                if (testStep != "") {
                    var grATFStep = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
                    if (grATFStep.get(testStep)) {
                        var outputName = this.getStepOutputField(grTestStep);
                        var testStepRef = this.buildRecordIDString(testStep,outputName);
                        // do a replaceAll for that sys_id in the original qry string
                        newQueryString.replaceAll(value, testStepRef);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

    },

    setStepNotes: function() {
        this.grATFStep.notes = 'Variables changed by the user during the recording';
    },

    type: 'SetVariableValuesTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-09-09 09:11:33</sys_created_on><sys_id>0cda1655dbb373001c4af53a2996197d</sys_id><sys_mod_count>18</sys_mod_count><sys_name>SetVariableValuesTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_0cda1655dbb373001c4af53a2996197d</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:32</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.ImpersonateUserTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>ImpersonateUserTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var ImpersonateUserTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
ImpersonateUserTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

	generateTestStep: function() {
		
		// If test recording user has not changed, there is no need for impersonation step
		if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.hasRecordingUserChanged()) {
			var impersonator;
			if (gs.nil(this.regressionObject.impersonate)) {
				impersonator = gs.getUserID();
			} else {
				impersonator = this.regressionObject.impersonate;
			} 

			this.grATFStep.inputs['user'] = impersonator;
			this.grATFStep.notes = "User who recorded the test.";

			TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
		}
	},
	
    type: 'ImpersonateUserTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-11-23 07:55:58</sys_created_on><sys_id>58c8d429db11c010f0a2f282399619bf</sys_id><sys_mod_count>13</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ImpersonateUserTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_58c8d429db11c010f0a2f282399619bf</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:28</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description/><global>false</global><ignore_in_now_experience>false</ignore_in_now_experience><name>SPVariableStateChecker</name><script><![CDATA[regress.SPVariableStateChecker = (function() {

    //Inherit from VariableStateChecker
    SPVariableStateChecker.prototype = Object.create(regress.VariableStateChecker.VariableStateChecker.prototype);
    SPVariableStateChecker.constructor = SPVariableStateChecker;

    function SPVariableStateChecker(gForm) {
        regress.VariableStateChecker.VariableStateChecker.call(this,gForm);
    }



    SPVariableStateChecker.prototype.getControl = function(field) {
        var control = this.gForm.getControl(field);

        return control;
    };

    SPVariableStateChecker.prototype.checkState = function(assertType, expected, field ) {

        var gForm = this.gForm;

        function getVisibility(field) {
			if (!field._visible || !field._parent)
				return field._visible;
			return getVisibility(gForm.getField(field._parent));
		}

        var result = true;

		if (gForm.hasField(field) == null && "visible" != assertType) { // field is not present on the form (but don't fail if we are checking visibility)
			return false;
		}

		var actualValue;

		if ("mandatory" == assertType)
			actualValue = gForm.isMandatory(field);
		else if ("read only" == assertType)
			actualValue = gForm.isReadOnly(field);
		else if ("visible" == assertType){
			var fromField = gForm.getField(field);
			actualValue = getVisibility(fromField);
        }
        
		if (expected != actualValue){ // failed
			result = false;
        }
        
		return result;
    };

    return {
        SPVariableStateChecker: SPVariableStateChecker,
        type: 'SPVariableStateChecker'
    };

})();]]></script><script_name/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-02-21 06:41:26</sys_created_on><sys_id>929c54d82fe2e4505a445e492799b6e0</sys_id><sys_mod_count>11</sys_mod_count><sys_name>SPVariableStateChecker</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_script_929c54d82fe2e4505a445e492799b6e0</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:23</sys_updated_on><ui_type>1</ui_type><use_scoped_format>false</use_scoped_format></sys_ui_script><sys_claim action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><claim_owner_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</claim_owner_scope><claim_timestamp>177c353866e0000001</claim_timestamp><metadata_update_name>sys_ui_script_929c54d82fe2e4505a445e492799b6e0</metadata_update_name><previous_claim_app_version>1.33</previous_claim_app_version><previous_claim_name>Regress - ATF Recorder</previous_claim_name><previous_claim_scope>86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</previous_claim_scope><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-02-21 06:42:47</sys_created_on><sys_id>4afc505c2fe2e4505a445e492799b64e</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>paul.morris</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2021-02-21 06:42:47</sys_updated_on></sys_claim></record_update>

It is best to use new data when created an ATF Test to minimise the dependencies on data. This will increase the success of the Test working in other environments or after System clones.

An Information Message will indicate if Regress is recording for the current record.  If not, please follow the Regress Configuration steps outlined previously.

When choosing a table to record, be mindful of the:

  • Supported User Interfaces
  • Supported Test Steps
  • Known Limitations
  • Suggested Use Cases

Please see the Support Documentation for more details.

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_processor"><sys_processor action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><class_name/><description/><interactive>false</interactive><name>Start Recording (Simple)</name><parameters/><params_endpoint/><path>startRecordingSimpleRegressionATFTest</path><path_endpoint/><require_csrf>false</require_csrf><roles>snc_internal</roles><script><![CDATA[(function process(g_request, g_response, g_processor) {
	var response = "";

	 if (!RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRecording()) {
		var recordingStarted = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.startRecording(null,"simple");
		var jsonParser = new JSON();
		response = jsonParser.encode(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getSessionDetails());
		g_response.sendRedirect(gs.getSession().getStack().pop());
		if (recordingStarted) {
			gs.addInfoMessage('⏺ Started Regress ATF Test Recorder. For best results, start by creating a new record.');
		}
	 } 
	
})(g_request, g_response, g_processor);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_processor</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-05-05 09:31:05</sys_created_on><sys_id>5443d55edbac58109e1014613996193a</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Start Recording (Simple)</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_processor_5443d55edbac58109e1014613996193a</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:25</sys_updated_on><type>script</type><xframe_sameorigin>false</xframe_sameorigin></sys_processor></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.OpenAnExistingRecordStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>OpenAnExistingRecordStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var OpenAnExistingRecordStepGenerator = Class.create();
OpenAnExistingRecordStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

	generateTestStep: function() {
		
		var previousRecordTestStepReference = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getPreviousRecordTestStepReference(this.regressionObject.sysID);
		if (!gs.nil(previousRecordTestStepReference)) {
			var grLastQueryStep = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
			if (grLastQueryStep.get(previousRecordTestStepReference)) {
				this.useQueryStep(grLastQueryStep);
				this.grATFStep.notes = 'Previously opened Record ' + this.regressionObject.display + ' was opened in this view.';	
				// Todo: find last Record Query and delete it, as it is not necessary
			}
		} else {
			
			this.setupOpenExistingForm();
		}

		this.grATFStep.inputs.view = this.regressionObject.viewName;
		TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
	},
	
	// Make reference to existing record if detected
	setupReferenceToPreviousRecord: function() {
		gs.debug('Setting up reference to previous record for Open Existing Record Test Step.');
		var grLastQueryStep = this.getLastTestStepWithRecordOutput(this.regressionObject.tableName);
		if (grLastQueryStep.isValidRecord()) {
			this.useQueryStep(grLastQueryStep);
			this.grATFStep.notes = 'Previously opened Record ' + this.regressionObject.display + ' was opened in this view.';
		} else {
			gs.warn('Something went wrong - could not find previous step with output');
			this.setupOpenExistingForm();
		}
		
	},
	
	setupOpenExistingForm: function() {
		gs.debug('Setting up reference to existing record for Open Existing Record Test Step.');
		
		var grLastQueryStep = this.getLastTestStepWithRecordOutput();
		
		if (grLastQueryStep.isValidRecord()) {
			this.useQueryStep(grLastQueryStep);
			this.grATFStep.notes = 'Existing Record ' + this.regressionObject.display + ' was opened in this view.';
		} else {
			gs.warn('Something went wrong - could not find previous step with output');
		}
		
	},

	
	useQueryStep: function(grLastQueryStep) {
		gs.debug('Using Output from  Step ' + grLastQueryStep.order);
		var outputField = this.getStepOutputField(grLastQueryStep);
		gs.debug('Output field is ' + outputField);
		var stepRefStr = this.buildRecordIDString(grLastQueryStep.getUniqueValue(),outputField );
		this.setContextualValueVariable('record_id',stepRefStr);
	},
	
	
	
    type: 'OpenAnExistingRecordStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-07-18 08:40:56</sys_created_on><sys_id>be871994db3233001c4af53a299619a4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>34</sys_mod_count><sys_name>OpenAnExistingRecordStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_be871994db3233001c4af53a299619a4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:30</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

Add Variable Set to Item</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
    var thisCatalogItem = current.getValue('sys_id');
	var addItem = gs.getProperty('regress.always.add.recorder.to.sc_cat_item','false');
	var isRegressEnabled = gs.getProperty('regress.enabled');
	
	if (addItem == 'false' || isRegressEnabled == 'false') {
		return;
	}
	
	var grCatalogVariableSets = new GlideRecord('io_set_item');
	grCatalogVariableSets.addEncodedQuery('sc_cat_item='+thisCatalogItem+'^variable_set=6df85e0ddb7f00109e101461399619f6');
	grCatalogVariableSets.query();

	if (!grCatalogVariableSets.hasNext()) {
		var catalogRecordingSetupUtil= new CatalogRecordingSetupUtil();
		// Add VS to this catalog item
		var qry = 'sys_id=' + thisCatalogItem;
		catalogRecordingSetupUtil.getCatalogItems(qry);
	}

})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sn-nerd</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2023-02-05 10:09:05</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>b21b86ce4734a110cef68a5f746d43c4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>16</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Regress - Add Variable Set to Item</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_b21b86ce4734a110cef68a5f746d43c4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-07 11:01:37</sys_updated_on><template/><when>after</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=b21b86ce4734a110cef68a5f746d43c4"/></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Used by Variable and Field State</description><name>AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

	setFieldState: function(fieldState) {
		this.fieldState = fieldState;
	},
	
	generateTestStep: function() {

		var isCaptureEnabled = this.captureMandatory 
		|| this.captureNotMandatory
		|| this.captureReadOnly
		|| this.captureNotReadOnlyMandatory
		|| this.captureHidden
		|| this.captureVisible;

		if (gs.nil(this.fieldState) || !isCaptureEnabled ) {
			this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();
		} else {
			this.setupFieldValidation();
		}

	},

	setMandatoryCapture: function(toggleValue) {
		this.captureMandatory = toggleValue;
	},

	setNotMandatoryCapture: function(toggleValue) {
		this.captureNotMandatory = toggleValue;		
	},

	setReadOnlyCapture: function(toggleValue) {
		this.captureReadOnly = toggleValue;		
	},

	setNotReadOnlyCapture: function(toggleValue) {
		this.captureNotReadOnly = toggleValue;		
	},

	setHiddenCapture: function(toggleValue) {
		this.captureHidden = toggleValue;		
	},

	setVisibleCapture: function(toggleValue) {
		this.captureVisible = toggleValue;		
	},
	
	isTestStepRequired: function() {
		var answer=true;

		var complexityLevel = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getRegressionLevel();
		
		var isSimpleFieldStatesEmpty = 
			gs.nil(this.fieldState.mandatory.toString()) 
			&& gs.nil(this.fieldState.hidden.toString()) 
			&& gs.nil(this.fieldState.readOnly.toString());

		var isExhaustiveFieldStatesEmpty = 
			gs.nil(this.fieldState.optional.toString()) 
			&& gs.nil(this.fieldState.visible.toString()) 
			&& gs.nil(this.fieldState.editable.toString());
		
		var nothingToRecord = gs.nil(this.fieldState.mandatory.toString()) 
		&& gs.nil(this.fieldState.hidden.toString()) 
		&& gs.nil(this.fieldState.readOnly.toString())
		&& gs.nil(this.fieldState.optional.toString()) 
		&& gs.nil(this.fieldState.visible.toString()) 
		&& gs.nil(this.fieldState.editable.toString());

		if (complexityLevel == 'exhaustive') {

			if (isSimpleFieldStatesEmpty && isExhaustiveFieldStatesEmpty) {
				answer = false;
			}
				
		} else if ((isSimpleFieldStatesEmpty && complexityLevel == "simple") || nothingToRecord) {
			answer = false;
		} 

		return answer;

	},

	setupFieldValidation: function() {
		var isTestStepRequired = this.isTestStepRequired();

		if (isTestStepRequired) {
			if (this.captureMandatory) {
				this.grATFStep.inputs.mandatory = this.fieldState.mandatory.toString();
			}
			if (this.captureHidden ) {
				this.grATFStep.inputs.not_visible = this.fieldState.hidden.toString();
			}
			if (this.captureReadOnly){
				this.grATFStep.inputs.read_only = this.fieldState.readOnly.toString();
			}

			if (this.captureNotMandatory) {
				this.grATFStep.inputs.not_mandatory = this.fieldState.optional.toString();
			}
			if (this.captureVisible) {
				this.grATFStep.inputs.visible = this.fieldState.visible.toString();
			}
			if (this.captureNotReadOnly) {
				this.grATFStep.inputs.not_read_only = this.fieldState.editable.toString();
			}

			TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);

		} else {
			this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();
		}
		

	},
	

	
    type: 'AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-07-17 08:43:01</sys_created_on><sys_id>276e0048db7633001c4af53a2996194e</sys_id><sys_mod_count>38</sys_mod_count><sys_name>AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_276e0048db7633001c4af53a2996194e</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:28</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>
