<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.TestGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>TestGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var TestGenerator = Class.create();

TestGenerator.prototype = {

    initialize: function(formState, grTest) {
		this.version = gs.getProperty('com.glide.embedded_help.version','').toLowerCase();
        this.addTestTemplate = new RegressAddTestTemplateAjax();

		
        if (gs.nil(grTest)) {
            var regressionLevel = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getRegressionLevel();
            grTest = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_test');
            grTest.initialize();
            grTest.name = regressionLevel.toUpperCase() + ' Regress Recording by ' + gs.getUserDisplayName();
          
            var description = this.generateTestDescription(regressionLevel);
            grTest.setValue('description',description);
        }

        if (!gs.nil(formState)) {
            this.formState = formState;
        }
		
		this.tableName = this.formState.tableName || "";
        this.grTest = grTest;
        this.log = [];
    },

    generateTestDescription: function(regressionLevel) {
        var testDescription = [];
        testDescription.push("Automatically generated Test using Regress ATF Recorder.");
        testDescription.push("Recording level: " + regressionLevel);
        testDescription.push("Recorded at: " + new GlideDateTime().getDisplayValue());
        testDescription.push("Recorded on: " + gs.getProperty('glide.war'));

        if (regressionLevel == "custom") {
            testDescription.push(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getCustomSettingsDetails());
        }

        return testDescription.join("\r\n");
    },

    useRecordActionTemplate: function() {
			if (this.formState.type == 'recordState_v1') {
		this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.record.snapshot.template');			
		} else {
		this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.record.action.template');
		}
    },

    useNewRecordTemplate: function() {
		this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.new.record.create.template');
    },

    useExistingRecordTemplate: function() {
		if (this.formState.type == 'recordState_v1') {
		    this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.record.snapshot.template');			
		} else if (this.formState.type == 'recordFormState_v1') {
		    this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.new.record.existing.template');		
		}

    },

    useAddToOrderGuideTemplate: function() {
        this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.reviewitem.orderguide.template');
    },

    useOpenOrderGuideSPTestTemplate: function() {
        this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.new.orderguide.template');
    },

    useServiceCatalogueViewTemplate: function() {
		this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.record.servicecatalog_cat_item_view');
    },

    useRecordProducerSPViewTemplate: function() {
        this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.record.recordproducer_cat_item_sp');
    },

    useServiceCatalogueSPViewTemplate: function() {
		this.templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.record.servicecatalog_cat_item_sp');
    },
	
	getMRVSTemplate: function() {
		var templateStepIds = this.getTestTemplate('regress.mrvs.template');
		
		return templateStepIds;
	},
	
	getTestTemplate: function(propertyName) {
        var testTemplateSysID = gs.getProperty(propertyName);	

		return this.getTestTemplateSteps(testTemplateSysID);
	},
	
    getTestTemplateSteps: function(sysID) {
        var testStepSysIDs = [];

        var grTestTemplate = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_test_template');

        if (!grTestTemplate.get(sysID)) {
            throw ("No Regression Test Generation rules exist for this configuration object. Please configure in Properties.");
        } else {
            testStepSysIDs = grTestTemplate.getValue('template').split(",");
        }

        // if create user is enabled
        if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCreateUserWhenImpersonating()) {
            testStepSysIDs = this.replaceImpersonateUserWithCreateUserTestStep(testStepSysIDs);
        }

        return testStepSysIDs;
    },

    replaceImpersonateUserWithCreateUserTestStep: function(testStepSysIDs) {

        var index = testStepSysIDs.indexOf(TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_IMPERSONATE_USER); 
        
        // There will only ever by one impersonation step per template
        if (index !== -1) { // imp user test step is found
            testStepSysIDs[index] = TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_CREATE_USER;
        }

        return testStepSysIDs;
    },

    setupTest: function() {
		var tableName = this.formState.tableName || "";
        var isCaptureOrderGuideEnabled = JSUtil.toBoolean(gs.getProperty('regress.enable.capture_order_guides','false'));

        switch (tableName) {
            case "ni": // UI16 Service Catalog
                this.useServiceCatalogueViewTemplate();
                break;
            case "": // SP Service Catalog
                if (NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.IsRecordProducer(this.formState.catalogItem)) {
                    this.useRecordProducerSPViewTemplate();
                } else { 
                    if (this.formState.partOfOrderGuide == true && isCaptureOrderGuideEnabled) {
                        this.useAddToOrderGuideTemplate();
                    } else {
                        if (NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.IsOrderGuide(this.formState.catalogItem) && isCaptureOrderGuideEnabled) {
                            this.useOpenOrderGuideSPTestTemplate();
                        } else {
                            this.useServiceCatalogueSPViewTemplate();
                        }
                    }
                }
                break;
            default: // UI16 Form
                this.generateTestForGlideForm();

        }

        return this.generateTestSteps();
    },

    

    generateTestSteps: function() {
        this.grTest.update();
        gs.info('Regress' + this.templateStepIds.length);

        this.addTestTemplate._setTestDescription(this.grTest.sys_id, this.templateStepIds);

        var nextOrder = this.addTestTemplate._getNextOrder(this.grTest.sys_id);

        for (var i = 0; i < this.templateStepIds.length; i++) {

            var catalogMRVSStepChecks = [
                TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM_SP,
                TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_NAVIGATE_WITHIN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP
            ];

			if (catalogMRVSStepChecks.indexOf(this.templateStepIds[i]) > -1  ) {
				var formVariables = this.formState.populatedVariableValues;

                // If MRVS was populated, cycle through to add in test steps just before submission or 'next' in order guide
				for ( var n in this.formState.multiRowVariableSetsState) {
					this.formState.mrvs = n; // Used in Add-Row Test Step set to determine the MRVS
					var mrvs = this.formState.multiRowVariableSetsState[n];
					for (var r in mrvs) {
						var row = mrvs[r];
						nextOrder = this.populateTestForMRVS(row, nextOrder);
					}
				}
				this.formState.populatedVariableValues = formVariables;
			}
			
			nextOrder = this.generateTestStep(this.templateStepIds[i], nextOrder);
        }
		
		var regressTestSysID = this.grTest.getUniqueValue();
		RegressATFRecordSessionv2.setATFTest(regressTestSysID);
		RegressATFRecordSessionv2.addRecordingDetailsToSession();
        return this.grTest.getValue('sys_id');
    },
	
	populateTestForMRVS: function(mrvsRow, nextOrder) {
		var mrvsTestSteps = this.getMRVSTemplate();
		this.formState.populatedVariableValues = mrvsRow;
		for (var i = 0; i <mrvsTestSteps.length; i++) {
			nextOrder = this.generateTestStep(mrvsTestSteps[i], nextOrder); 
		}
		
		return nextOrder;
	},
	
	generateTestStep: function(templateStepId, nextOrder) {
		var grATFStep = this.addTestTemplate._createStep(this.grTest.sys_id, templateStepId, this.tableName , nextOrder);
        var testStepWorker = TestStepGenerator.GetTestStepWorker(grATFStep, this.formState);
        testStepWorker.generateTestStep();
		nextOrder++;	
		
		return nextOrder;
	},

    generateTestForGlideForm: function() {
        var grRegressionObject = new GlideRecord(this.formState.tableName);
        grRegressionObject.get(this.formState.sysID);

        if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRecordingRecord(grRegressionObject)) {
            // If we are already recording the record, just capture the actions taken
            this.useRecordActionTemplate();
        } else {
            if (this.formState.isNewRecord == true) {
                this.useNewRecordTemplate();

            } else {
                this.useExistingRecordTemplate();
            }
        }
		
		RegressATFRecordSessionv2.addPrimaryRecord(grRegressionObject);
    },

    createTest: function() {
        return grTest.update();
    },

    deleteTest: function() {
        this.grTest.deleteRecord();
    },

    addLog: function(msg) {
        this.log.push(msg);
    },

    type: 'TestGenerator'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-06-18 10:44:54</sys_created_on><sys_id>a1b3df6adbc233001c4af53a2996193c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>257</sys_mod_count><sys_name>TestGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_a1b3df6adbc233001c4af53a2996193c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:30</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_processor"><sys_processor action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><class_name/><description/><interactive>false</interactive><name>Start Recording (Actions only)</name><parameters/><params_endpoint/><path>startRecordingActionsRegressionATFTest</path><path_endpoint/><require_csrf>false</require_csrf><roles>snc_internal</roles><script><![CDATA[(function process(g_request, g_response, g_processor) {
	var response = "";

	 if (!RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRecording()) {
		var recordingStarted = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.startRecording(null,"actions");
		var jsonParser = new JSON();
		response = jsonParser.encode(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getSessionDetails());
		g_response.sendRedirect(gs.getSession().getStack().pop());
		if (recordingStarted) {
			gs.addInfoMessage('⏺ Started Regress ATF Test Recorder. For best results, start by creating a new record.');
		}
	 } 


	
})(g_request, g_response, g_processor);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_processor</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-05-05 09:24:41</sys_created_on><sys_id>bac11d9adbac58109e101461399619fd</sys_id><sys_mod_count>3</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Start Recording (Actions only)</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_processor_bac11d9adbac58109e101461399619fd</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:26</sys_updated_on><type>script</type><xframe_sameorigin>false</xframe_sameorigin></sys_processor></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_fix"><sys_script_fix action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><before>false</before><description/><name>Regress - Add Recorder Variable Set</name><record_for_rollback>true</record_for_rollback><script><![CDATA[exec();

function getCatalogItems(encQry) {
    var grCatalogItem = new GlideRecord('sc_cat_item');
    grCatalogItem.addEncodedQuery(encQry);
    grCatalogItem.query();
    while (grCatalogItem.next()) {
        addRegressRecorderToVariableSet(grCatalogItem.getUniqueValue());
    }
}

function addRegressRecorderToVariableSet(scCatItemSysID) {
    var grCatalogVariableSet = new GlideRecord('io_set_item');
    grCatalogVariableSet.newRecord();
    grCatalogVariableSet.setValue('variable_set', '6df85e0ddb7f00109e101461399619f6');
    grCatalogVariableSet.setValue('sc_cat_item', scCatItemSysID);
    // This prevents it being captured in Update Set
    grCatalogVariableSet.setWorkflow(false);

    return grCatalogVariableSet.insert();
}

function exec() {
    var catalogItemFilter = new GlideRecord('sys_filter');
    var catalogItemFilterSysID = gs.getProperty('regress.record.all.items.filter', 'e06d59a02f17a4105a445e492799b6d1');
    if (catalogItemFilter.get(catalogItemFilterSysID)) {
        getCatalogItems(catalogItemFilter.getValue('filter'));
    }
}]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_fix</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sn-nerd</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2023-02-13 11:51:18</sys_created_on><sys_id>bc7f63e84749e910cef68a5f746d4333</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Regress - Add Recorder Variable Set</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_fix_bc7f63e84749e910cef68a5f746d4333</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-13 11:51:18</sys_updated_on><unloadable>false</unloadable></sys_script_fix></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_include_524174a72faee4105a445e492799b64c
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.EmailTestGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>EmailTestGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var EmailTestGenerator = Class.create();
EmailTestGenerator.prototype = {
    initialize: function(grATFTestSysID, formGDT) {
        this.grATFTestSysID = grATFTestSysID;
        this.formGDT = formGDT;
    },

    regressNotifications: function (recordSysId, tableName, testStepId) {
        var emailInfo = this.getEmailsForRecord(recordSysId, tableName);

        return this.createTestsForEmails(recordSysId, emailInfo,testStepId);
    },


    // look at sys email first
    getEmailsForRecord: function(recordSysId, tableName) {
        var emailDataArray = [];
        var grEmail = new GlideRecord('sys_email');
        // Only look for emails recorded during the recording
        grEmail.addEncodedQuery('instance='+ recordSysId+'^target_table=' + tableName +'^sys_created_on>' + this.formGDT );
        grEmail.query();

        while (grEmail.next()) {

            var emailData = {};
            var grEmailLog = this.getEmailLogDetails(grEmail);
            var isTriggeredByNotification = grEmailLog.isValidRecord();
            emailData.recipients = grEmail.recipients.toString();
            emailData.subject = grEmail.getValue('subject');
            if (isTriggeredByNotification) {
                emailData.trigger = "source_notification";
                emailData.triggerSysID = grEmailLog.getValue('notification');          
            } else  {
                var flowSysID = this.getTriggeringFlowSysID(grEmail);
                if (!gs.nil(flowSysID)) {
                    emailData.triggerSysID = flowSysID;
                    emailData.trigger = "source_flow";
                } else {
                    emailData.trigger = "unknown";
                }
            }
            emailData.emailLogRecord = grEmailLog.getUniqueValue();
            emailDataArray.push(emailData); 

        }

        return emailDataArray;
    },

    getTriggeringFlowSysID: function(grEmail) {
        var answer;
        ////X-ServiceNow-Source:FlowDesigner-ef6c0234a85be4107de964034785abbc
        var flowPattern = /X-ServiceNow-Source:FlowDesigner-([a-f0-9]{32})/;
        var headers = grEmail.getValue('headers');
        var reg = new RegExp(flowPattern);
        var matches = reg.exec(headers);
        if (!gs.nil(matches) && matches.length == 2) {
            // Header contains sys_id of flow context, which references the triggering flow
            var flowContextID = matches[1];
            var grFlowContext = this.getFlowContextBySysID(flowContextID);
            if (grFlowContext.isValidRecord()) {
                answer = grFlowContext.getValue('flow');
            }
            
        }

        return answer;
    },

    getFlowContextBySysID: function(flowContextSysID) {
        var grFlowContext = new GlideRecord('sys_flow_context');
        grFlowContext.get(flowContextSysID);

        return grFlowContext;
    },

    getEmailLogDetails: function(grEmail) {
        var grEmailLog = new GlideRecord("sys_email_log");
        grEmailLog.addQuery('email',grEmail.getUniqueValue());
        grEmailLog.addNotNullQuery('notification');
        grEmailLog.addQuery('sys_created_on','>',this.formGDT);
        grEmailLog.query();
        grEmailLog.next();

        return grEmailLog;
    },

    createTestsForEmails: function(recordSysId, emailData,testStepId) {

        var testSteps = [];
        for (var i in emailData) {
            var regressionObject = {};
            regressionObject.recordSysId = recordSysId;
            regressionObject.testStepId = testStepId;
            regressionObject.sourceSysID = emailData[i].triggerSysID;
            regressionObject.recipients = emailData[i].recipients;
            regressionObject.sourceField = emailData[i].trigger;
            regressionObject.subject = emailData[i].subject;
            var stepConfigId;

            if (regressionObject.sourceField  == "source_notification") {
                // Test Step 'Validate Outbound Email Generated by Notification is currently buggy (KB0863789)
                if ( !RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotificationsAsRecordQuery() ) {
                    stepConfigId = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL_GENERATED_BY_NOTIFICATION');
                } else {
                    //this will use the sys_email record as a regression object, similar to taking a snapshot
                    regressionObject = this.getRegressionObjectforEmail(emailData[i].emailLogRecord, regressionObject.subject,regressionObject);
                    stepConfigId = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY');
                }
            } else if (regressionObject.sourceField  == "source_flow") {
                stepConfigId = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL_GENERATED_BY_FLOW');
            } else {
                stepConfigId = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL');
            }
            
            if (!gs.nil(stepConfigId)) {
                var grAtfStep = this.createTestForEmail(regressionObject, stepConfigId);
                testSteps.push(grAtfStep.getUniqueValue());
            }
        }

        return testSteps;
    },

    // Workaround function to Notification Query Step issue (KB0863789)
    getRegressionObjectforEmail: function(emailLogSysID, subject, emailRegressionObject) {
        var regressionObject = {
            sysID: emailLogSysID,
            tableName: 'sys_email_log',
            display: subject,
            existingRecordQuery: '',
            isNewRecord: false,
            type: 'recordState_v1'
        };
        var testStepRecordReference = TestStepGenerator.BuildRecordIDString(emailRegressionObject.testStepId, "record_id");
        var testStepTableReference = TestStepGenerator.BuildRecordIDString(emailRegressionObject.testStepId, "table");
        var notification = "notification=" + emailRegressionObject.sourceSysID;
        var instanceCondition = "email.instance=" + testStepRecordReference;
        var tableCondition = "email.target_table=" + testStepTableReference; 
        var typeCondition = "email.typeINsend-ignored,send-ready,sent";
        var recipientsCondition = "email.recipients=" + emailRegressionObject.recipients;

        var conditionsArray = [notification,instanceCondition,tableCondition,typeCondition,recipientsCondition];
		var encQry = conditionsArray.join("^") + "^EQ";

        regressionObject.existingRecordQuery = encQry;


        return regressionObject;
    },

    createTestForEmail: function(regressionObject,stepConfigId) {
        var testStepCreator = new RegressAddTestTemplateAjax();
        var grAtfStep = testStepCreator._createStep(this.grATFTestSysID, stepConfigId,null,0);
        var testStepGen = TestStepGenerator.GetTestStepWorker(grAtfStep,regressionObject);
        testStepGen.generateTestStep();

        return grAtfStep;
    },

    type: 'EmailTestGenerator'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-03-03 10:32:20</sys_created_on><sys_id>524174a72faee4105a445e492799b64c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>69</sys_mod_count><sys_name>EmailTestGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_524174a72faee4105a445e492799b64c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:27</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.SetFieldValuesTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>SetFieldValuesTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var SetFieldValuesTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
SetFieldValuesTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(SetValuesTestStepGenerator, {


    initialize: function(grATFStep, regressionObject) {
        SetValuesTestStepGenerator.prototype.initialize.call(this, grATFStep, regressionObject);
        this.regressionField = "populatedFieldValues";
        this.inputStepField = "field_values";
    },

    generateStepsForValues: function() {
        gs.info('SetFieldValuesTestStepGenerator generateStepsForValues');
        var fieldValuesWithNoDependencies = this.handleFieldDependencies();
        gs.info('We have these fields ' + this.fieldValues);
        SetValuesTestStepGenerator.prototype.generateStepsForValues.call(this,fieldValuesWithNoDependencies);
        gs.info('end of func generateStepsForValues');
    },

    handleFieldDependencies: function() {
        // Get a list of fields which are dependencies for fields we want to set
        var fieldDependencies = this.getFieldDependencies(this.fieldValues);

        // Find if those dependencies are being set in this step
        var fieldsToSplit = this.getDependentFields(fieldDependencies);
        gs.debug("We need to split out these fields into individual steps:" + fieldsToSplit.join(","))
        var fieldValuesWithNoDependencies = this.fieldValues;

        // We need to remove these, as ATF prevents save of a Test Step with dependent fields
        if (fieldsToSplit && fieldsToSplit.length > 0) {
            fieldValuesWithNoDependencies = this.removeFieldDependencies(fieldsToSplit);
        }

        gs.debug('First step with no dependencies: ' + fieldValuesWithNoDependencies);
        // If we found field dependencies with our original test step, we will split them into multiple steps
        if (fieldsToSplit && fieldsToSplit.length > 0) {
            this.splitTestStepByFieldDependencies(fieldsToSplit);
        }

        return fieldValuesWithNoDependencies;
    },

    removeFieldDependencies: function(dependentFieldsToSplit) {
        gs.debug('removing field dependencies');
        var fieldValuesWithoutDependents = this.fieldValues;
        var numOfDependentFields = dependentFieldsToSplit.length;

        // Remove all dependent fields from current field values
        for (var i = 0; i < numOfDependentFields; i++) {
            
            var field = dependentFieldsToSplit[i];
            gs.debug('for field ' + field);
            var regexPattern = new RegExp('\\^*' + field + '=[^\\^]*', 'gi'); // e.g. "category=XYZ^"... or "category=XYZ"
            fieldValuesWithoutDependents = fieldValuesWithoutDependents.replace(regexPattern, "");
        }

        gs.debug('removed field dependencies:'+fieldValuesWithoutDependents);

        return fieldValuesWithoutDependents;
    },

    splitTestStepByFieldDependencies: function(dependentFieldsToSplit) {

        var originalFieldValues = this.regressionObject.populatedFieldValues.toString();
        var numOfDependentFields = dependentFieldsToSplit.length;
        gs.debug("Trying to split " + dependentFieldsToSplit.join(",") + " into " + numOfDependentFields + " steps.");
        gs.debug("Original field values: " + originalFieldValues);
        // Remove all dependent fields from current field values
        for (var i = 0; i < numOfDependentFields; i++) {

            var field = dependentFieldsToSplit[i];
            var regexPattern = new RegExp(field + '=[^\\^]*', 'gi'); // e.g. "category=XYZ^"... or "category=XYZ"
            var dependentSetValue = originalFieldValues.match(regexPattern);
            gs.debug("Splitting " + field);
            gs.debug("dependentSetValue: " +dependentSetValue);
            // This hack stops the next Test Step 'validate field state' coming before the dependency split
            this.grATFStep.order = parseInt(this.originalOrder, 10)+1;
            if (dependentSetValue && dependentSetValue.length > 0) {
                gs.debug("Matched on " + dependentSetValue[0])
                this.generateSetValuesTestStep(dependentSetValue[0], "Field was split as it is dependent on another field");
            }
        }

    },

    //Adapted from BR
    getFieldDependencies: function() {
        var table = this.grATFStep.inputs['table'];
        var queryString = new GlideQueryString(table, this.fieldValues);
        queryString.deserialize();
        var terms = queryString.getTerms();
        var dependentFields = {};
        var td = GlideTableDescriptor.get(table);
        for (var i = 0; i < terms.size(); i++) {
            var term = terms.get(i);
            var field = term.getField() + "";
            if (gs.nil(field))
                continue;

            var ed = td.getElementDescriptor(field);
            if (ed) {
                var dependentField = ed.getDependent();
                if (!gs.nil(dependentField))
                    dependentFields[field] = dependentField + "";
                else
                    dependentFields[field] = "";
            }
        }

        return dependentFields;
    },

    // get the list of fields that are dependent on other fields set in this step
    getDependentFields: function(dependentFields) {
        var fields = Object.keys(dependentFields);
        var fieldsToMove = [];
        for (var i = 0; i < fields.length; i++) {
            var dependentField = dependentFields[fields[i]];
            if (!gs.nil(dependentField) && fields.indexOf(dependentField) != -1)
                fieldsToMove.push(fields[i]);
        }
        if (fieldsToMove.length == 0)
            return "";

        return fieldsToMove;
    },


    type: 'SetFieldValuesTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-07-17 08:16:54</sys_created_on><sys_id>d658c4c0db7633001c4af53a299619b4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>76</sys_mod_count><sys_name>SetFieldValuesTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_d658c4c0db7633001c4af53a299619b4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-24 12:40:04</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description/><global>false</global><ignore_in_now_experience>false</ignore_in_now_experience><name>VariableStateChecker</name><script><![CDATA[regress.VariableStateChecker = (function() {

    function VariableStateChecker(gForm) {
        this.mandatory = [];
        this.readOnly = [];
        this.hidden = [];
        this.optional = [];
        this.editable = [];
        this.visible = [];

        this.readOnlyAndPopulated = [];

        if (typeof gForm == "undefined") {
            this.gForm = regress.common.gForm;
        } else {
            this.gForm = gForm;
        }
    }

    VariableStateChecker.prototype.getAllStates = function() {
        return {
            mandatory: this.mandatory,
            readOnly: this.readOnly,
            hidden: this.hidden,
            optional: this.optional,
            editable: this.editable,
            visible: this.visible
        };
    };

    VariableStateChecker.prototype.getState = function(name, refName) {
        this.determineIfMandatory(name, refName);
        this.determineIfReadOnly(name, refName);
        this.determineIfVisible(name, refName);
    };

    VariableStateChecker.prototype.determineIfMandatory = function(name, refName) {

        var isMandatory = this.checkState('mandatory', true, name);

        if (isMandatory) {
            this.mandatory.push(refName);
        } else {
            this.optional.push(refName);
        }

        return isMandatory;
    };

    VariableStateChecker.prototype.determineIfReadOnly = function(name, refName) {

        var isReadOnly = this.checkState('read only', true, name);

        if (isReadOnly) {
            this.readOnly.push(refName);

            var varValue = this.gForm.getValue(name);
            if (varValue != "") {
                var encString = "IO:" + refName + "=" + varValue;
                this.readOnlyAndPopulated.push(encString);
            }
        } else {
            this.editable.push(refName);
        }

        return isReadOnly;
    };

    VariableStateChecker.prototype.determineIfVisible = function(name, refName) {

        var isVisible = this.checkState('visible', true, name);

        if (isVisible) {
            this.visible.push(refName);
        } else {
            this.hidden.push(refName);
        }

        return isVisible;
    };

    VariableStateChecker.prototype.checkState = function(assertType, expected, field) {

        var fieldGE = this.gForm.getGlideUIElement(field);

        // Always considered hidden, not read only, not mandatory if not on form
        if (this.isNotOnForm(assertType,field, fieldGE)) {
            return false;
        }

        var result = true;
        var actualValue;
        var control = this.getControl(field);

       actualValue = this.determineState(assertType,field,fieldGE,control);

        if (expected != actualValue) {
            result = false;
        }

        return result;
    };

    VariableStateChecker.prototype.isNotOnForm = function(assertType,fieldGE) {
        var answer = false;
        if (fieldGE == null && "visible" != assertType) { // field is not present on the form (but don't fail if we are checking visibility)
            answer = true;
        }

        return answer;
    };

    VariableStateChecker.prototype.getControl = function(field) {
        var control = this.gForm.getControl(field);
        if (!control)
            control = this.gForm.getNiBox(field);

        return control;
    };

    VariableStateChecker.prototype.determineState = function(assertType,field,fieldGE,control ) {
        var actualValue;
        if ("mandatory" == assertType)
            actualValue = !!this.gForm.isMandatory(field);
        else if ("read only" == assertType)
            actualValue = (!fieldGE || !control) ? false : !!this.gForm.isReadOnly(fieldGE, control);
        else if ("visible" == assertType)
            actualValue = (!fieldGE || !control) ? false : !!this.gForm.isVisible(fieldGE, control);

        return actualValue;
    };





    return {
        VariableStateChecker: VariableStateChecker,
        type: 'VariableStateChecker'
    };

})();]]></script><script_name/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-02-13 08:33:49</sys_created_on><sys_id>6299abe92f5e6c105a445e492799b673</sys_id><sys_mod_count>10</sys_mod_count><sys_name>VariableStateChecker</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_script_6299abe92f5e6c105a445e492799b673</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:23</sys_updated_on><ui_type>10</ui_type><use_scoped_format>false</use_scoped_format></sys_ui_script></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_fix_423cd1a02f17a4105a445e492799b618
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_fix"><sys_script_fix action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><before>false</before><description>Add the Variable Set 'Regress Recorder' to all Catalog Items, so Regress will run on all of them (provided the Scripts have been added to the Service Portal Theme).

This script below can be copied and ran as a Background Script in the appropriate scope, to update items in that scope.

DO NOT RUN MORE THAN ONCE
</description><name>Regress - Enable Regress for All Items</name><record_for_rollback>true</record_for_rollback><script><![CDATA[(function exec() {
    var catalogRecordingSetupUtil = new CatalogRecordingSetupUtil();
	catalogRecordingSetupUtil.addVariableSetToAllItems();
	var portalRecordingSetupUtil = new PortalRecordingSetupUtil();
	portalRecordingSetupUtil.addUIScriptsToAllThemes();
	gs.setProperty('regress.always.add.recorder.to.sc_cat_item','true');
})();]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_fix</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-03-31 12:45:21</sys_created_on><sys_id>423cd1a02f17a4105a445e492799b618</sys_id><sys_mod_count>13</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Regress - Enable Regress for All Items</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_fix_423cd1a02f17a4105a445e492799b618</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-06 10:40:06</sys_updated_on><unloadable>true</unloadable></sys_script_fix></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_include_2d50a60147b06110cef68a5f746d431b
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.CatalogRecordingSetupUtil</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>CatalogRecordingSetupUtil</name><script><![CDATA[var CatalogRecordingSetupUtil = Class.create();
CatalogRecordingSetupUtil.prototype = {
    initialize: function() {
    },

    getCatalogItems: function(encQry) {
        var grCatalogItem = new GlideRecord('sc_cat_item');
        grCatalogItem.addEncodedQuery(encQry);
        grCatalogItem.query();

        while (grCatalogItem.next()) {
            this.addRegressRecorderToVariableSet(grCatalogItem.getUniqueValue());
        }
    },

    addRegressRecorderToVariableSet: function(scCatItemSysID) {
        var grCatalogVariableSet = new GlideRecord('io_set_item');
        grCatalogVariableSet.newRecord();
        grCatalogVariableSet.setValue('variable_set', '6df85e0ddb7f00109e101461399619f6');
        grCatalogVariableSet.setValue('sc_cat_item', scCatItemSysID);
        // This prevents it being captured in Update Set
        grCatalogVariableSet.setWorkflow(false);

        return grCatalogVariableSet.insert();
    },

	addVariableSetToAllItems: function() {
		//get all catalog items without the regress variable set
		var allCatalogItemsQuery = 'active=true^sys_class_name=pc_hardware_cat_item^ORsys_class_name=pc_software_cat_item^ORsys_class_name=sc_cat_item^ORsys_class_name=sc_cat_item_guide^ORsys_class_name=sc_cat_item_producer';
		this.getCatalogItems(allCatalogItemsQuery);
		
	},
	
    setupVariableSets: function() {
        var catalogItemFilter = new GlideRecord('sys_filter');
        var catalogItemFilterSysID = gs.getProperty('regress.record.all.items.filter', 'e06d59a02f17a4105a445e492799b6d1');
        if (catalogItemFilter.get(catalogItemFilterSysID)) {
            this.getCatalogItems(catalogItemFilter.getValue('filter'));
        }
    },

    type: 'CatalogRecordingSetupUtil'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2023-02-02 09:07:19</sys_created_on><sys_id>2d50a60147b06110cef68a5f746d431b</sys_id><sys_mod_count>10</sys_mod_count><sys_name>CatalogRecordingSetupUtil</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_2d50a60147b06110cef68a5f746d431b</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-07 10:50:21</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.CreateUserTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>CreateUserTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var CreateUserTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
CreateUserTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

	generateTestStep: function() {
		
		// If test recording user has not changed, there is no need for impersonation step
		if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.hasRecordingUserChanged()) {
			var currentUser = gs.getUser();
			this.grATFStep.inputs['first_name'] = "[Regress] " + currentUser.firstName;
			this.grATFStep.inputs['last_name'] = currentUser.lastName;
			// Methods below return a JavaObject, must be converted to string for glidelist field
			var roleNames = currentUser.getRoles().toArray().join(",");
			var roleSysIDs;
			if (gs.hasRole('admin')) {
				roleSysIDs = this.getRoleSysIDs('admin');
			} else {
				roleSysIDs = this.getRoleSysIDs(roleNames);
			}
			
			this.grATFStep.inputs['roles'] = roleSysIDs;

			var currentGrUser = this.getGRForCurrentUser();
			this.grATFStep.inputs['field_values'] = this.getFieldsFromUser(currentGrUser);
			this.grATFStep.inputs['groups'] = currentUser.getMyGroups().toArray().join(","); 
			this.grATFStep.notes = "Create and Impersonate temporary user based on user who was recorded (" + currentUser.getDisplayName() + ")";
			RegressATFRecordSessionv2.setLastRecordingToCurrentUser();
			//Impersonate defaults to true
			TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
		} else {
			this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();
		}
	},

	getRoleSysIDs: function(roleNames) {
		var roleSysIDs = [];
		var grRole = new GlideRecord('sys_user_role');
		grRole.addQuery('name','IN',roleNames);
		grRole.query();
		while(grRole.next()) {
			roleSysIDs.push(grRole.getUniqueValue());
		}

		return roleSysIDs.join(",");
	},

	getGRForCurrentUser: function() {
		var grUser = new GlideRecord('sys_user');
		grUser.get(gs.getUserID());

		return grUser;
	},

	getFieldsFromUser: function(gr) {
		var hashmap = {};
		var fieldsQry='';
		var ignoreFields = {
			'sys_created_on':true,
			'sys_created_by':true,
			'sys_updated_on':true,
			'sys_updated_by':true,
			'first_name':true,
			'last_name':true,
			'last_login':true,
			'last_login_device':true,
			'sys_id':true,
			'sys_class_name':true,
			'user_password':true,
			'sys_mod_count':true,
			'avatar':true,
			'calendar_integration':true,
			'enable_multifactor_authn':true,
			'failed_attempts':true,
			'geolocation_tracked':true,
			'source':true,
			'user_name': true,
			'hashed_user_id' : true,
			'last_login_time' : true
		};
		var encQryLines = [];
		var glideRecordUtil = new GlideRecordUtil();
		glideRecordUtil.populateFromGR(hashmap,gr,ignoreFields);

		for (var i in hashmap) {
			encQryLines.push(i + "=" + hashmap[i]);
		}

		fieldsQry = encQryLines.join("^") + "^EQ";

		return fieldsQry;
	},
	
    type: 'CreateUserTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-04-11 03:09:30</sys_created_on><sys_id>b8c5dca2db0014109e10146139961926</sys_id><sys_mod_count>27</sys_mod_count><sys_name>CreateUserTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_b8c5dca2db0014109e10146139961926</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-02 11:50:58</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.RegressAddTestTemplateAjax</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Extended  AddTestTemplateAjax to make some efficiency modification</description><name>RegressAddTestTemplateAjax</name><script><![CDATA[var RegressAddTestTemplateAjax = Class.create();
RegressAddTestTemplateAjax.prototype = Object.extendsObject(AddTestTemplateAjax, {

	_createStep: function(testId, stepConfigId, testTableName, order) {
		var gr = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
		gr.initialize();
		gr.test = testId;
		gr.order = order;
		gr.step_config = stepConfigId;
		// Set the variable only if the step has a valid table input variable and the testTableName passed is not null
		if (gr.inputs.getVariablesRecord().isValidField('table') && !gs.nil(testTableName))
			gr.inputs.table = testTableName;
		//gr.insert(); //Was causing issues with input variables, making them not populate 
		
		return gr; // not returned in orginal function
	},
	
	// Descriptions become too big if we update them each time a template is applied, so lets not update it.
	_setTestDescription: function() {
		
	},

    type: 'RegressAddTestTemplateAjax'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-06-27 07:13:29</sys_created_on><sys_id>221a7069db1233001c4af53a29961954</sys_id><sys_mod_count>14</sys_mod_count><sys_name>RegressAddTestTemplateAjax</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_221a7069db1233001c4af53a29961954</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:27</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.RegressATFRecordSessionv2Ajax</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>true</client_callable><description/><name>RegressATFRecordSessionv2Ajax</name><script><![CDATA[var RegressATFRecordSessionv2Ajax = Class.create();
RegressATFRecordSessionv2Ajax.prototype = Object.extendsObject(global.AbstractAjaxProcessor, {
	
	isRecording: function() {
		var answer = global.RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRecording();
		
		return answer;
	},
	
	stopRecording: function() {
		global.RegressATFRecordSessionv2.stopRecording();
	},
	
	startExhaustiveRecording: function() {
		var recordingStarted;
		if (!RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRecording()) {
			recordingStarted = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.startRecording(null, "exhaustive");
		}
		
		return recordingStarted;
	},
	
	isRegressEnabledForTable: function() {
		var tableName = this.getParameter('sysparm_table_name');
		var answer = global.RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRegressEnabledForTable(tableName);
		
		return answer;
	},
	
	canRecordForServicePortal: function() {

		var isRecording = global.RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRecording();
		var recordingMsg = global.RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getRecordingMsg();
		var answer = {
			canRecordForTable: isRecording, 
			recordingMsg:recordingMsg,
			isRecording:isRecording,
			timeout:gs.getProperty('regressui.exec.timeout',1000)
		};
		var json = new JSON();		

		return json.encodeObject(answer);	
	},
	
	canRecordForTable: function() {
		var tableName = this.getParameter('sysparm_table_name');
		return this._canRecordForTable(tableName);
	
	},
	
	_canRecordForTable:function(tableName) {
		var isTableEnabled = global.RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRegressEnabledForTable(tableName);
		var isRecording = global.RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isRecording();
		var recordingMsg = global.RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getRecordingMsg();
		var answer = {
			canRecordForTable: isTableEnabled && isRecording, 
			recordingMsg:recordingMsg,
			isRecording:isRecording,
			timeout:gs.getProperty('regressui.exec.timeout',1000)
		};
		var json = new JSON();
		
		return json.encodeObject(answer);			
	},
	
    type: 'RegressATFRecordSessionv2Ajax'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-02-20 10:20:41</sys_created_on><sys_id>a05f0f02db4fc0109e10146139961973</sys_id><sys_mod_count>24</sys_mod_count><sys_name>RegressATFRecordSessionv2Ajax</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_a05f0f02db4fc0109e10146139961973</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:29</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="catalog_script_client"><catalog_script_client action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><applies_catalog>true</applies_catalog><applies_extended>false</applies_extended><applies_req_item>false</applies_req_item><applies_sc_task>false</applies_sc_task><applies_target_record>false</applies_target_record><applies_to>set</applies_to><cat_item/><cat_variable/><condition/><description/><field/><global>true</global><isolate_script>true</isolate_script><messages/><name>Regress Submit (SP)</name><order/><script><![CDATA[function onSubmit() {

	try {
		var isUIScriptsLoaded = (typeof regress != 'undefined');
		if (isUIScriptsLoaded && regress.reg_form.isRecording()) {
			var isOrderGuide = g_service_catalog.isOrderGuide();
			// UI Script does not respect object inheritance in SPFormSnapShot properly
			// so it must be called from Client Script (only way it seems to work)
			var regressSnapshot = new regress.ServiceCatalogFormSP.SPFormSnapShot(g_form, isOrderGuide);
			regressSnapshot.takeSnapShot();
			regressSnapshot.addSnapshotToCurrentTest();
		} 
	} catch (e) {
		g_form.addErrorMessage("Regress UI Error: Something went wrong and the a form snapshot could not be created for the catalog item. Check the console for more details.");
		console.log("Regress UI Error for catalog item with sys_id " + g_form.getUniqueValue());
		console.log(e);
	} finally {
		return true;
	}
	
}

sys_update_xml.payload:
true
On the System Properties page, click 'Show more options' and add an additional tables you would like to record.


When opening an existing record that has not previously been naviaged to in the recording sessions, Regress will create a 'Record Query' Step to find records that are similar to the record you opened. This is because the record opened may not be present in all of your ServiceNow environments, or may change state after recording the test.

The query will be based on the mandatory fields present on the form. The query will check that all these fields are populated.

Then, it will query for records with matching values based on the fields shown above. Fields are filtered based on the tables that recording is enabled for. The following fields will be matched by Default:

  • Approver
  • Item
  • SLA Definition
  • Stage
  • State

Add any additional that might be useful to compare records.

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.CatalogItemTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>CatalogItemTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var CatalogItemTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
CatalogItemTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

	generateTestStep: function() {
		this.grATFStep.inputs['catalog_item'] = this.regressionObject.catalogItem;
		if (this.regressionObject.servicePortal) {
			var spSuffix = this.regressionObject.servicePortal;
			var portalSysID = this.getPortalSysIdFromSuffix(spSuffix);
			this.grATFStep.inputs['portal_id'] = portalSysID;
		}
		TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
	},

	getPortalSysIdFromSuffix: function(portalSuffix) {
		var portalSysID;
		var grServicePortal = new GlideRecord('sp_portal');
		grServicePortal.addQuery('url_suffix',portalSuffix);
		grServicePortal.query();
		if (grServicePortal.next()) {
			portalSysID = grServicePortal.getUniqueValue();
		}

		return portalSysID;
	},
	
    type: 'CatalogItemTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-09-09 09:08:55</sys_created_on><sys_id>193a9ad1dbb373001c4af53a29961949</sys_id><sys_mod_count>3</sys_mod_count><sys_name>CatalogItemTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_193a9ad1dbb373001c4af53a29961949</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:32</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.FieldStateValidationTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>33f637e8c3ba220076173b0ac3d3aee1</description><name>FieldStateValidationTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var FieldStateValidationTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
FieldStateValidationTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator, {

	generateTestStep: function() {
		var complexityLevel = RegressATFRecordSessionv2.getRegressionLevel();
		
		if (complexityLevel != 'actions') {
			this.setFieldState(this.regressionObject.fieldState); 
			this.grATFStep.notes = 'The field state of the form when a UI action is clicked during the recording.';
			this.setMandatoryCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingMandatoryFields());
			this.setNotMandatoryCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotMandatoryFields());
			this.setVisibleCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingVisibleFields());
			this.setHiddenCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotVisibleFields());
			this.setReadOnlyCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingReadonlyFields());
			this.setNotReadOnlyCapture(RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotReadonlyFields());
			
			AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
		}
	},
	
    type: 'FieldStateValidationTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-01-07 09:48:52</sys_created_on><sys_id>78222080db1680109e10146139961967</sys_id><sys_mod_count>5</sys_mod_count><sys_name>FieldStateValidationTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_78222080db1680109e10146139961967</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:29</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.ClickUIActionTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>ClickUIActionTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var ClickUIActionTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
ClickUIActionTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

	generateTestStep: function() {
		

		this.grATFStep.inputs['ui_action'] = this.regressionObject.uiAction;
		
		if (this.isClientSideUIAction()) {
			// Client side UI Actions can affect field values and field state, which gets checked before the UI action is clicked
			// This will cause the Test to fail. To avoid this, we simply move the click to before the field validations occur
			// Note that some Client UI Actions will just use the sysverb_update and will look like server side to Regress.
			gs.debug('Client Side UI Action was clicked');
			this.grATFStep.notes = "Client Side UI Action clicked.";	
			this.makeFieldValidationStepsInactive();
		} else {
			this.grATFStep.notes = "The UI Action clicked by the user.";
		}
		TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
		
		RegressATFRecordSessionv2.addTestStepMarker(
			this.regressionObject.sysID, 
			this.regressionObject.tableName,
			this.grATFStep.getValue('sys_id')
			);
	},
	
	isClientSideUIAction: function() {
		var grClientSideUIAction = new GlideRecord("sys_ui_action");
		grClientSideUIAction.addQuery("sys_id", this.regressionObject.uiAction);
		grClientSideUIAction.addQuery('client',true);
		grClientSideUIAction.query();
		
		return grClientSideUIAction.hasNext();
	},
	
	makeFieldValidationStepsInactive: function() {
		var grLastQueryStep;

		var absValidation = new AbstractStateValidationTestStepGenerator(this.grATFStep,this.regressionObject);
		absValidation.setFieldState(this.regressionObject.fieldState);
		var hasFieldStateValidation = absValidation.isTestStepRequired();

		// Mark any validation steps inactive, as UI action may have changed this which will mess up ATF
		if (hasFieldStateValidation) {
			grLastQueryStep = this.getLastTestStep(TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_FIELD_STATE_VALIDATION);
			if (grLastQueryStep.isValidRecord()) {
				this.deactivePreviousStep(grLastQueryStep);
			}
		}
		/*
		absValidation.setFieldState(this.regressionObject.variableState);
		var hasVarialeStateValidation = absValidation.isTestStepRequired();

		if (hasVarialeStateValidation) {
			grLastQueryStep = this.getLastTestStep(TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VARIABLE_STATE_VALIDATION);
			if (grLastQueryStep.isValidRecord()) {
				this.deactivePreviousStep(grLastQueryStep);
			}
		}*/

		if (!gs.nil(this.regressionObject.changedFieldValues) && this.regressionObject.changedFieldValues != '') {
			grLastQueryStep = this.getLastTestStep(TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_FIELD_VALUES_VALIDATION);
			if (grLastQueryStep.isValidRecord()) {
				this.deactivePreviousStep(grLastQueryStep);
			}			
		}

		if (!gs.nil(this.regressionObject.validateVariableValues) && this.regressionObject.validateVariableValues != '') {
			grLastQueryStep = this.getLastTestStep(TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_VARIABLE_VALUES);
			if (grLastQueryStep.isValidRecord()) {
				this.deactivePreviousStep(grLastQueryStep);
			}			
		}
	},

	isAnyValidations: function(fieldState) {
		var answer = false;
		if (!gs.nil(fieldState)) {
			var nothingToRecord = gs.nil(fieldState.mandatory.toString()) 
			&& gs.nil(fieldState.hidden.toString()) 
			&& gs.nil(fieldState.readOnly.toString())
			&& gs.nil(fieldState.optional.toString()) 
			&& gs.nil(fieldState.visible.toString()) 
			&& gs.nil(fieldState.editable.toString());
			answer = !nothingToRecord;
			gs.info("fieldState:" + fieldState.hidden.toString());
			gs.info("fieldState:" + fieldState.readOnly.toString());
			gs.info("fieldState:" + fieldState.optional.toString());
			gs.info("fieldState:" + fieldState.visible.toString());
			gs.info("fieldState:" + fieldState.editable.toString());
			gs.info("fieldState:" + fieldState.mandatory.toString());
			gs.info("answer:" + answer);
		}

		return answer;
	},

	deactivePreviousStep: function(grLastQueryStep) {
		grLastQueryStep.active = false;
		grLastQueryStep.notes = "Field/Variable state and/or values may have been changed by Client side UI Action that would cause this Test to fail. Reactivate these steps if the Action did not make any changes to these.";	
		grLastQueryStep.update();
	},

	
    type: 'ClickUIActionTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-11-24 03:21:23</sys_created_on><sys_id>f373a8b5db5dc010f0a2f2823996196c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>38</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ClickUIActionTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_f373a8b5db5dc010f0a2f2823996196c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:31</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>This class is responsible for sending the regression details to the server and managing the form state snapshot class.</description><global>false</global><ignore_in_now_experience>false</ignore_in_now_experience><name>RegressUI</name><script><![CDATA[var regress = regress || {};
regress.common = {};

regress.common.gForm = '';
regress.common.gUser = '';
regress.common.gSCForm = '';

regress.common.log = function (msg) {

    function log(msg) {
        if (typeof jslog !== "undefined") {
            jslog(msg);
        } else {
            // jslog not supported in SP
            console.log(msg);
        }
    }

    var prefix = "[REGRESS] ";

    if (typeof msg == "object") {
        log(prefix + "Object output:");
    } else {
        msg = prefix + msg;
    }

    log(msg);
};

regress.reg_form = (function () {
    "use strict";

    var readyToRecord = false;
    var uiType;
    var formSnapshot = null;
    var recordingMsg;
    var isSilent = false;

    return {

        initialise: function(gForm, gUser, gSCForm, showRecordingMsg) {
            if (typeof showRecordingMsg == 'undefined') {
                isSilent = false;
            }

            isSilent = showRecordingMsg;

            try {
                if (typeof gForm == 'undefined') {
                    regress.common.gForm = window.g_form;
                    regress.common.log('found GlideForm from window');
                } else {
                    regress.common.gForm = gForm;
                }
                if (typeof gUser == 'undefined') {
                    regress.common.gUser = window.g_user;
                    regress.common.log('found GlideUser from window');
                }
                if (typeof gSCForm == 'undefined') {
                    regress.common.gSCForm = window.g_sc_form;
                    regress.common.log('found Variable Editor from window');
                }

                regress.common.log('Table name is ' + regress.common.gForm.getTableName());
                var ga = new GlideAjax('RegressATFRecordSessionv2Ajax');
                ga.addParam('sysparm_name','canRecordForTable');
                ga.addParam('sysparm_table_name',regress.common.gForm.getTableName());
                ga.getXMLAnswer(isRecordingCallback);	
        
            } catch (e) {
                regress.common.log('Could not get Glide Globals. Must pass in as params');
            }
        },

        getFormSnapshot: function() {
            return formSnapshot;
        },

        getFormState: function () {
            return formSnapshot.recordFormState;
        },

        isRecording: function () {
            return readyToRecord;
        },

        getUIType: function() {
            return uiType;
        },

        logCurrentFormState: function () {
            var formStateJSON = JSON.stringify(formSnapshot.recordFormState);
            regress.common.log(formStateJSON);
        },

        recordAction: function() {
            var success = true;
            if (readyToRecord) {
                this.takeSnapshot();
                var success = formSnapshot.addSnapshotToCurrentTest();
            } else {
                success = false;
                regress.common.log('Regress is not recording or scripts are not loaded');
            }

            return success;
        },

        setFormSnapshot: function(newFormSnapshot) {
            formSnapshot = newFormSnapshot;
        },

        takeSnapshot: function() {

            if (readyToRecord) {
                formSnapshot.takeSnapshot(); 
                regress.common.log('Snapshot taken');
            }

            jslog(this.getFormState());
            this.logCurrentFormState();
            return this.getFormState();
        },

    canSnapshotField : function(fieldName) {
        return formSnapshot.canSnapshotField(fieldName);
    },

	snapshotField: function(fieldName) {
		return formSnapshot.snapshotField(fieldName); 
	},
        type: 'RegressUI'

    };

    function isRecordingCallback(xmlResponse) {
        try {
            var regressDetails = JSON.parse(xmlResponse);
            if (regressDetails.isRecording == false) {
                regress.common.log("Regress is not currently recording.");
            } else if (regressDetails.canRecordForTable == true) {
                regress.common.isRecording = true;
                recordingMsg = regressDetails.recordingMsg;
                loadScripts();
            } else {
                regress.common.log("Regress is not configured to record for this table.");
            }
       } catch(e) {
            regress.common.gForm.addErrorMessage("Regress has failed to load. Error: " + e);
        }
        
    }

    function loadScripts() {
        var requiredScripts = [];
        if (window == null || regress.common.gForm.getTableName() == null) {
            uiType = "ServicePortal_ServiceCatalog";
            regress.common.log('Loading Scripts for Service Portal UI');
            scriptsLoadedCallback();

        } else if (regress.common.gForm) {
            regress.common.log('Loading Scripts for UI16...');
            requiredScripts.push("VariableStateChecker.jsdbx");
            requiredScripts.push("ServiceCatalogForm17.jsdbx");

            if (regress.common.gForm.getTableName() != "ni") {
                requiredScripts.push("GlideFormUI16.jsdbx");
                requiredScripts.push("FieldStateChecker.jsdbx");
                regress.common.log('Loading Scripts for GlideForm UI16...');
            }
            ScriptLoader.getScripts(requiredScripts,scriptsLoadedCallback);
        }
        

    }

    function scriptsLoadedCallback() {
        regress.common.log('Scripts Loaded, ready to snapshot!');
        if (!isSilent) {
            regress.common.gForm.addInfoMessage(recordingMsg);
        }
        var tableName = regress.common.gForm.getTableName();
        if (tableName == "ni") {
            formSnapshot =  new regress.ServiceCatalogForm17.FormSnapshot();
            uiType = "UI16_ServiceCatalog";
        } else if (tableName != null) {
            uiType = "UI16_GlideForm";
            formSnapshot =  new regress.GlideFormUI16.GlideFormSnapshot();
        } else {
            uiType = "SP_ServiceCatalog";
            formSnapshot = new regress.ServiceCatalogFormSP.SPFormSnapShot();
        }
        regress.common.log("UI Detected was :" + uiType);



        readyToRecord = true;

    }

})();]]></script><script_name/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-11-28 09:58:15</sys_created_on><sys_id>e8a46a83db99c410f0a2f28239961922</sys_id><sys_mod_count>498</sys_mod_count><sys_name>RegressUI</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_script_e8a46a83db99c410f0a2f28239961922</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-17 11:05:37</sys_updated_on><ui_type>10</ui_type><use_scoped_format>false</use_scoped_format></sys_ui_script></record_update>
