<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.TestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>TestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var TestStepGenerator = Class.create();

//MISC
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_IMPERSONATE_USER = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_IMPERSONATE_USER');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_CREATE_USER = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_CREATE_USER');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL_GENERATED_BY_NOTIFICATION = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL_GENERATED_BY_NOTIFICATION');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL_GENERATED_BY_FLOW = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL_GENERATED_BY_FLOW');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL');

//GLIDEFORM
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY_DEPRECATED = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY_DEPRECATED');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_AN_EXISTING_RECORD = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_AN_EXISTING_RECORD');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_NEW_FORM = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_NEW_FORM');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_SET_FIELD_VALUES = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_SET_FIELD_VALUES');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_FIELD_STATE_VALIDATION = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_FIELD_STATE_VALIDATION');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_FIELD_VALUES_VALIDATION = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_FIELD_VALUES_VALIDATION');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_CLICK_UI_ACTION = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_CLICK_UI_ACTION');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_UI_ACTION_VISIBILITY = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_UI_ACTION_VISIBILITY');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VARIABLE_STATE_VALIDATION = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VARIABLE_STATE_VALIDATION');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_SET_VARIABLE_VALUES = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_SET_VARIABLE_VALUES');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_VARIABLE_VALUES = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_VARIABLE_VALUES');
//CATALOG ITEM
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_CATALOG_ITEM = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_CATALOG_ITEM');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_CATALOG_ITEM_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_CATALOG_ITEM_SP');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_SET_VARIABLE_VALUES_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_SET_VARIABLE_VALUES_SP');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VARIABLE_STATE_VALIDATION_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VARIABLE_STATE_VALIDATION_SP');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_VARIABLE_VALUES_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_VARIABLE_VALUES_SP');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ADD_ROW_TO_MULTI_ROW_VARIABLE_SET_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_ADD_ROW_TO_MULTI_ROW_VARIABLE_SET_SP');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM_SP');
//ORDER GUIDE
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_NAVIGATE_WITHIN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_NAVIGATE_WITHIN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_REVIEW_ITEM_IN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_REVIEW_ITEM_IN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_REVIEW_ORDER_GUIDE_SUMMARY_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_REVIEW_ORDER_GUIDE_SUMMARY_SP');
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_SUBMIT_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_SUBMIT_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP');

//RECORD PRODUCER
TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_RECORD_PRODUCER_SP = gs.getProperty('Regress.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_RECORD_PRODUCER_SP');

TestStepGenerator.BuildRecordIDString = function(stepSysID, outputField) {
    // Example string: {{step['e0f46d2ddb9233001c4af53a299619f9'].first_record}}

    var stepStrFormat = "step['{0}'].{1}";
    var stepStr = gs.getMessage(stepStrFormat, [stepSysID, outputField]);

    return "{{" + stepStr + "}}"; // Could not work out how to escape {} in gs.getMessage
};

TestStepGenerator.GetTestStepWorker = function(grATFStep, regressionObject) {
    var testStepWorker;

    switch (grATFStep.getValue('step_config')) {
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_IMPERSONATE_USER:
            testStepWorker = new ImpersonateUserTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_CREATE_USER:
            testStepWorker = new CreateUserTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY_DEPRECATED:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY:
            testStepWorker = new RecordQueryTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_AN_EXISTING_RECORD:
            testStepWorker = new OpenAnExistingRecordStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_NEW_FORM:
            testStepWorker = new OpenNewFormTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_UI_ACTION_VISIBILITY:
            testStepWorker = new VisibleUIActionTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_SET_FIELD_VALUES:
            testStepWorker = new SetFieldValuesTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_FIELD_VALUES_VALIDATION:
            testStepWorker = new FieldValuesValidationTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_FIELD_STATE_VALIDATION:
            testStepWorker = new FieldStateValidationTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_CLICK_UI_ACTION:
            testStepWorker = new ClickUIActionTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_CATALOG_ITEM:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_CATALOG_ITEM_SP:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_RECORD_PRODUCER_SP:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_REVIEW_ITEM_IN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP:
            testStepWorker = new CatalogItemTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_NAVIGATE_WITHIN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP:
            testStepWorker = new NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_SET_VARIABLE_VALUES:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_SET_VARIABLE_VALUES_SP:
            testStepWorker = new SetVariableValuesTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_VARIABLE_VALUES_SP:
            testStepWorker = new ValidateVariableValuesSPTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VARIABLE_STATE_VALIDATION:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VARIABLE_STATE_VALIDATION_SP:
            testStepWorker = new VariableStateValidationTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM_SP:
            testStepWorker = new OrderCatalogueItemTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
		case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ADD_ROW_TO_MULTI_ROW_VARIABLE_SET_SP:
            testStepWorker = new AddRowToMRVSSPTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;		
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL_GENERATED_BY_NOTIFICATION:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL_GENERATED_BY_FLOW:
        case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_VALIDATE_OUTBOUND_EMAIL:
            testStepWorker = new OutboundEmailTestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
            break;
        default:
            testStepWorker = new TestStepGenerator(grATFStep, regressionObject);
    }

    return testStepWorker;
};

TestStepGenerator.prototype = {

    initialize: function(grATFStep, regressionObject) {
        this.grATFStep = grATFStep;
        this.regressionObject = regressionObject;
        this.grATFStep.notes = "Automatically generated using Regress";
        this.originalOrder = grATFStep.getValue('order') + 0;
        this.log = [];
    },

	getLastTestStepOrder: function() {
		var lastTestStepOrder = "0";
		var countTestStep = new GlideAggregate('sys_atf_step');
		countTestStep.addQuery('test', this.grATFStep.test);
		countTestStep.addAggregate("MAX","order");
		countTestStep.query();
		
		while (countTestStep.next()) {
			lastTestStepOrder = parseInt(countTestStep.getAggregate("MAX","order"));
		}
		return lastTestStepOrder;
	},
	
    generateTestStep: function() {
		var maxOrder = this.getLastTestStepOrder();
		var currentOrder = this.grATFStep.getValue('order');
		// Prevent subsequent test steps from messing up order for field value dependency test step splits
		if (currentOrder <= maxOrder) {
			this.grATFStep.setValue('order',maxOrder+1);
		}
        this.grATFStep.update();
    },

    setContextualValueVariable: function(inputVariable, value) {
        // First we need to update the record, otherwise the input field will be populated, but trust me - it won't work!
        this.grATFStep.update();
        // inputs.record_id is stored in sys_element_mapping table 
        this.grATFStep.inputs[inputVariable] = value;

        // This is not generated until an attempt to set inputs
        this.grATFStep.update();

        // Now the sys_element_mapping record exists, but for some reason, record_id is always empty regardless of what gets put in inputs
        var elementMapping = this.getRecordIDInputVar(inputVariable);

        // So we have to manually populate it by manipulating what is in sys_element_mapping
        // Even setting inputs.record_id after the sys_element_mapping is created doesn't update it after save
        var foundElementMapping = elementMapping.isValidRecord();

        if (foundElementMapping) {
            elementMapping.value = value;
            elementMapping.update();
        } else {
            this.log('Could not retrieve element mapping for test step.');
        }

        return foundElementMapping;
    },

    getTestStepsBetween: function(low, high) {
        var grLastQueryStep = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('test', this.grATFStep.test);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('order', '>', low);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('order', '<', high);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('sys_id', '!=', this.grATFStep);
        grLastQueryStep.orderByDesc('order');
        grLastQueryStep.query();

        return grLastQueryStep;
    },

    getTestStepsAfterCurrentStep: function() {
        var afterOrder = this.grATFStep.getValue('order');
        var grLastQueryStep = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('test', this.grATFStep.test);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('order', '>=', afterOrder); // Order may not have changed yet, so just in case
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('sys_id', '!=', this.grATFStep);
        grLastQueryStep.orderByDesc('order');
        grLastQueryStep.query();

        return grLastQueryStep;
    },

    getLastTestWithRequestOutput: function() {
        var beforeOrder = this.grATFStep.getValue('order');
        var grLastQueryStep = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('test', this.grATFStep.test);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM_SP)
            .addOrCondition('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM)
            .addOrCondition('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_A_RECORD_PRODUCER_SP)
            .addOrCondition('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_SUBMIT_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('order', '<', beforeOrder);
        grLastQueryStep.orderByDesc('order');
        grLastQueryStep.query();
        if (grLastQueryStep.next() ) {
            gs.debug('Step ' + grLastQueryStep.getValue('order') + ' found for Catalogue Output ');         
        }

        return grLastQueryStep;
    },

    getLastTestWithUserOutput: function() {
        var beforeOrder = this.grATFStep.getValue('order');
        var grLastQueryStep = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('test', this.grATFStep.test);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_CREATE_USER)
            .addOrCondition('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_IMPERSONATE_USER);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('order', '<', beforeOrder);
        grLastQueryStep.orderByDesc('order');
        grLastQueryStep.query();
        //gs.info(grLastQueryStep.getEncodedQuery());
        if (grLastQueryStep.next() ) {
            gs.debug('Step ' + grLastQueryStep.getValue('order') + ' found for User Output ');         
        }

        return grLastQueryStep;
    },

    
    replaceCurrentUserSysIDWithStepRef: function(populatedFieldValues) {
        // sub out current user for test step reference ('user')
        var currentUserSysID = gs.getUserID();
        var recordIDString;

        // replace with a test step reference
        var grUserTestStep = this.getLastTestWithUserOutput();
        if (grUserTestStep.isValidRecord()) {
            var recordIDString = this.buildRecordIDString(grUserTestStep.getUniqueValue(),'user');
            populatedFieldValues = populatedFieldValues.replaceAll("="+currentUserSysID, "="+recordIDString);
        } 

        return populatedFieldValues;
    },
    getLastTestStepWithRecordOutput: function(tableName) {

        var beforeOrder = this.grATFStep.getValue('order');
        var grLastQueryStep = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('test', this.grATFStep.test);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM_SP)
            .addOrCondition('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM)
            .addOrCondition('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY)
        .addOrCondition('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY_DEPRECATED)
            .addOrCondition('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_CLICK_UI_ACTION)
            .addOrCondition('step_config', TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_AN_EXISTING_RECORD);
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('order', '<', beforeOrder);
        grLastQueryStep.orderByDesc('order');
        grLastQueryStep.query();
        while (grLastQueryStep.next()) {
            if (!gs.nil(tableName)) {
                if (grLastQueryStep.inputs.hasOwnProperty('table') && grLastQueryStep.inputs.table == tableName) {
                    break;
                }
            } else {
                break;
            }

        }

        gs.debug('Step ' + grLastQueryStep.getValue('order') + ' has table of ' + grLastQueryStep.inputs.table);

        return grLastQueryStep;
    },

    getLastTestStep: function(stepConfigSysID, afterOrder) {
        var beforeOrder = this.grATFStep.getValue('order');
        var grLastQueryStep = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
        grLastQueryStep.addQuery('test', this.grATFStep.test);
        if (stepConfigSysID)
            grLastQueryStep.addQuery('step_config', stepConfigSysID);
            grLastQueryStep.addQuery('order', '<', beforeOrder);
        if (!gs.nil(afterOrder)) {
            grLastQueryStep.addQuery('order', '>', afterOrder);
        }
        if (!gs.nil(beforeOrder)) {
            grLastQueryStep.addQuery('order', '<', beforeOrder);
        }
        grLastQueryStep.orderByDesc('order');
        grLastQueryStep.addActiveQuery();
        grLastQueryStep.query();
        grLastQueryStep.next();

        //should do a table check here too...
        return grLastQueryStep;
    },

    getRecordIDInputVar: function(inputVariable, testStepID) {

        if (gs.nil(testStepID)) {
            testStepID = this.grATFStep.getValue('sys_id');
        }

        var elementMapping = new GlideRecord('sys_element_mapping');
        elementMapping.addQuery('id', testStepID);
        elementMapping.addQuery('field', inputVariable);
        elementMapping.query();
        elementMapping.next();

        return elementMapping;
    },

    buildRecordIDString: function(stepSysID, outputField) {
        // Moved to static function, as I needed this outside of the class
        return TestStepGenerator.BuildRecordIDString(stepSysID, outputField);
    },

    getStepOutputField: function(grLastQueryStep) {
        var stepConfig = grLastQueryStep.getValue('step_config');
        var outputField;
        switch (stepConfig) {
            case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY:
            case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_RECORD_QUERY_DEPRECATED:
                outputField = 'first_record';
                break;
            case TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_ORDER_A_CATALOG_ITEM:
                outputField = 'request_id';
                break;
            default:
                outputField = 'record_id';
        }

        return outputField;
    },

    log: function(msg) {
        this.log.push(msg);
        gs.info(msg);
    },

    type: 'TestStepGenerator'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-07-17 08:11:40</sys_created_on><sys_id>293784c0db7633001c4af53a299619d8</sys_id><sys_mod_count>131</sys_mod_count><sys_name>TestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_293784c0db7633001c4af53a299619d8</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-24 12:15:25</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>false</active><api_name>global.UIPolicyRegression</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>UIPolicyRegression</name><script><![CDATA[var UIPolicyRegression = Class.create();
UIPolicyRegression.prototype = Object.extendsObject(RegressionObject, {

	initialize: function(grUIPolicy) {
		RegressionObject.prototype.initialize.call(this,grUIPolicy);
		this.tableName = grUIPolicy.getValue('table');
		this.conditions = grUIPolicy.conditions;
		this.parseFieldValidation();
		this.viewName = 'default';
		if (grUIPolicy.getValue('global') == false) {
			this.viewName = grUIPolicy.view.name;
		}
		
	},
	
	parseFieldValidation: function() {
		// TODO: reverse is false tests
		var mandatoryFieldState = new PolicyActionToFieldStateStepProcessor('mandatory');
		var hiddenFieldState = new PolicyActionToFieldStateStepProcessor('visible');
		var disabledFieldState = new PolicyActionToFieldStateStepProcessor('disabled');
		var grUIPolicyActions = this.getUIPolicyActions();
		
		while(grUIPolicyActions.next()) {
			mandatoryFieldState.processPolicyAction(grUIPolicyActions);
			hiddenFieldState.processPolicyAction(grUIPolicyActions);
			disabledFieldState.processPolicyAction(grUIPolicyActions);
		}
		
		this.mandatoryFields = mandatoryFieldState.getIsFieldState();
		this.notMandatoryFields = mandatoryFieldState.getIsNotFieldState();
		this.visibleFields = hiddenFieldState.getIsFieldState();
		this.notVisibleFields = hiddenFieldState.getIsNotFieldState();
		this.readOnlyFields = disabledFieldState.getIsFieldState();
		this.notReadOnlyFields = disabledFieldState.getIsNotFieldState();
	},
	
	getUIPolicyActions: function() {
		var grUIPolicyActions = new GlideRecord('sys_ui_policy_action');
		grUIPolicyActions.addQuery('ui_policy=' + this.sys_id);
		grUIPolicyActions.addActiveQuery();
		grUIPolicyActions.query();
		
		return grUIPolicyActions;
	},
	
	type: 'UIPolicyRegression'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-07-24 09:07:13</sys_created_on><sys_id>b607945adb3233001c4af53a299619d2</sys_id><sys_mod_count>12</sys_mod_count><sys_name>UIPolicyRegression</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_b607945adb3233001c4af53a299619d2</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:30</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator = Class.create();

NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.IsRecordProducer = function(catItemSysID) {

    var answer;
    var grCatItem = new GlideRecord('sc_cat_item_producer');
    grCatItem.addQuery("sys_id",catItemSysID);
    grCatItem.query();
    answer = grCatItem.hasNext();
    
    return answer
};

NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.IsOrderGuide = function(catItemSysID) {

    var answer;
    var grCatItem = new GlideRecord('sc_cat_item_guide');
    grCatItem.addQuery("sys_id",catItemSysID);
    grCatItem.query();
    answer = grCatItem.hasNext();
    
    return answer
};

NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.CHOOSE_OPTIONS_GUIDE_STEP = 2;
NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.SUMMARY_GUIDE_STEP = 3;

NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

    generateTestStep: function() {
		
         if (NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.IsOrderGuide(this.regressionObject.catalogItem)) {
            this.grATFStep.inputs['guide_step'] = NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.CHOOSE_OPTIONS_GUIDE_STEP;
        } else {
            this.grATFStep.inputs['guide_step'] = NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.SUMMARY_GUIDE_STEP;
            this.deactivateRedundantSteps();
        }

        TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);
		
	},

    deactivateRedundantSteps: function() {
        var grOpenOrderGuideStep = this.getLastTestStep(TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_OPEN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP);
        if (grOpenOrderGuideStep.isValidRecord()) {
   
            var afterOrder = grOpenOrderGuideStep.getValue('order');
            var beforeOrder =  this.grATFStep.getValue('order');

            // Each previous order guide template is generating these steps
            // We only want the last ones to be active
            var stepsToDeactivate = [
                TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_NAVIGATE_WITHIN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP,
                TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_SUBMIT_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP
            ]

            for (var i in stepsToDeactivate) {
                var grStep = this.getLastTestStep(stepsToDeactivate[i],afterOrder, beforeOrder);
                if (grStep.isValidRecord() ) {
                    // Ignore the first test step for navigation to 'choose options'
                    if (grStep.getValue('step_config') == TestStepGenerator.STEP_CONFIG_NAVIGATE_WITHIN_AN_ORDER_GUIDE_SP)  {
                        if (grStep.inputs['guide_step'] == NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator.CHOOSE_OPTIONS_GUIDE_STEP) {
                            continue;
                        }
                    }
                    grStep.setValue('active',false);
                    grStep.setValue('notes','Another Catalogue Item was added after this one, so these steps are not needed');
                    grStep.update();
                }
            }
            
        }
    },

    type: 'NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-03-13 09:58:06</sys_created_on><sys_id>215904b62f3260105a445e492799b67b</sys_id><sys_mod_count>11</sys_mod_count><sys_name>NavigateWithinAnOrderGuideTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_215904b62f3260105a445e492799b67b</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:27</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.PortalRecordingSetupUtil</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>PortalRecordingSetupUtil</name><script><![CDATA[var PortalRecordingSetupUtil = Class.create();
PortalRecordingSetupUtil.prototype = {
    initialize: function() {},
	
    exec: function() {
        var servicePortalFilter = new GlideRecord('sys_filter');
        var catalogItemFilterSysID = gs.getProperty('regress.apply.ui.script.filter', 'e86367572f73a0105a445e492799b690');
        if (servicePortalFilter.get(catalogItemFilterSysID)) {
            this.getServicePortals(servicePortalFilter.getValue('filter'));
        }
    },

    addUIScriptsToAllThemes: function() {
        this.getServicePortals('');
    },

    getServicePortals: function(encQry) {
        var grServicePortal = new GlideAggregate('sp_portal');
        grServicePortal.addEncodedQuery(encQry);
        grServicePortal.addQuery('theme', '!=', 'NULL');
        grServicePortal.groupBy('theme');
        grServicePortal.query();
        while (grServicePortal.next()) {
            this.addUIScriptsToTheme(grServicePortal.getValue('theme'));
        }
    },

    addUIScriptsToTheme: function(themeSysID) {
        // RegressUI
        this.addUIScriptToTheme(themeSysID, 'e8a46a83db99c410f0a2f28239961922', 0, "RegressUI");
        // 17
        this.addUIScriptToTheme(themeSysID, 'f0fc23ed2f5e6c105a445e492799b696', 1, "ServiceCatalogForm17");
        // SP
        this.addUIScriptToTheme(themeSysID, 'c7391cd6db210010f0a2f282399619f0', 2, 'ServiceCatalogFormSP');
    },

    addUIScriptToTheme: function(themeSysID, uiScriptID, order, displayName) {
        var jsInclude = this.createJSInclude(uiScriptID, displayName);
        var grUIScriptTheme = new GlideRecord('m2m_sp_theme_js_include');
        grUIScriptTheme.initialize();
        grUIScriptTheme.setValue('sp_theme', themeSysID);
        grUIScriptTheme.setValue('sp_js_include', jsInclude);
        grUIScriptTheme.setValue('order', order);

        // Prevent this from being captured in the current update set
        grUIScriptTheme.setWorkflow(false);

        return grUIScriptTheme.insert();
    },

    createJSInclude: function(uiScriptID, displayName) {
        var grJSInclude = new GlideRecord('sp_js_include');
        grJSInclude.initialize();
        grJSInclude.setValue('sys_ui_script', uiScriptID);
        grJSInclude.setValue('source', 'local');
        grJSInclude.setValue('display_name', displayName);

        // Prevent this from being captured in the current update set
        grJSInclude.setWorkflow(false);

        return grJSInclude.insert();

A Test is of little value until it has been shown to Pass.

Execute the Test that was generated to validate that all pertinant details were recorded as expected.

In some circumstances the Test may not pass and manual adjustment is required. Reasons include:

  • User input not detected/supported by Regress
  • Too many fields populated at one time resulting in Client Scripts / UI Policies not running
  • Form interceptors used to create new records

Please raise any defects on the Regress Patreon.

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.RegressSystemPropertyHelper</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>RegressSystemPropertyHelper</name><script><![CDATA[var RegressSystemPropertyHelper = Class.create();


RegressSystemPropertyHelper.GetExistingAllowedTables = function() {
        var defaults;
        var sysIDs = [];
        var allowedTableNames = gs.getProperty('regress.record.for.tables', 'task,sys_approval_approver,task_sla,sc_req_item');
        var grTables = new GlideRecord('sys_db_object');
        grTables.addQuery('name', 'IN', allowedTableNames);
        grTables.query();
        while (grTables.next()) {
            sysIDs.push(grTables.getUniqueValue());
        }
        defaults = sysIDs.join(",");

        return defaults;
    },

    RegressSystemPropertyHelper.GetTableNamesBySysIDs = function(sysDbObjectSysIDs) {
        var tableNames = [];
        var grTables = new GlideRecord('sys_db_object');
        grTables.addQuery('sys_id', 'IN', sysDbObjectSysIDs.toString());
        grTables.query();
        while (grTables.next()) {
            tableNames.push(grTables.getValue('name'));
        }

        return tableNames.join(",");
    };

RegressSystemPropertyHelper.GetExistingRecordFieldFilterByTableSysIDs = function(sysDbObjectSysIDs) {
    var tableNamesCSV = RegressSystemPropertyHelper.GetTableNamesBySysIDs(sysDbObjectSysIDs);
    var qry = "nameIN" + tableNamesCSV + "^internal_type!=collection^column_label!=";

    return qry;
};

RegressSystemPropertyHelper.GetSelectedFieldNames = function(csvSysIDs) {
    var grDictionaryEntry = new GlideRecord('sys_dictionary');
    var fieldNames = [];
    grDictionaryEntry.addQuery('sys_id', 'IN', csvSysIDs);
    grDictionaryEntry.query();

    while (grDictionaryEntry.next()) {
        fieldNames.push(grDictionaryEntry.getValue('element'));
    }

    return fieldNames.join();
};

RegressSystemPropertyHelper.GetExistingRecordFieldDefaultValues = function() {
    var defaults = '';
    var fieldSysIDs = [];
    var existingQry = "nameIN" + gs.getProperty('regress.record.for.tables', 'task,sys_approval_approver,task_sla,sc_req_item');
    var fieldNames = gs.getProperty('regress.existing.query.fields', "state,type,stage,cat_item");
    var grDictionaryEntry = new GlideRecord('sys_dictionary');
    grDictionaryEntry.addEncodedQuery(existingQry);
    grDictionaryEntry.addQuery('elementIN' + fieldNames);
    grDictionaryEntry.query();

    while (grDictionaryEntry.next()) {
        fieldSysIDs.push(grDictionaryEntry.getUniqueValue());
    }


    return fieldSysIDs.join(",");
};

RegressSystemPropertyHelper.prototype = {
    initialize: function() {},

    resetPropertiesToDefault: function() {
		gs.setProperty('regress.always.add.recorder.to.sc_cat_item','false');
        gs.setProperty('regress.enabled', 'false');
        gs.setProperty('regress.regression.level', "simple");
        gs.setProperty('regress.existing.query.fields', "stage,stage,description,approver,description,state,sla,cat_item,state" );
        gs.setProperty('regress.record.for.tables', "task,sc_req_item,task_sla,sysapproval_approver");
		gs.setProperty('regress.create.new.user.when.impersonating','true');

    },

    updateSystemProperty: function(name, value) {
        gs.setProperty(name,value);
    },

    type: 'RegressSystemPropertyHelper'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-01-05 07:08:47</sys_created_on><sys_id>18d8695bdb0600109e10146139961916</sys_id><sys_mod_count>49</sys_mod_count><sys_name>RegressSystemPropertyHelper</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_18d8695bdb0600109e10146139961916</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-16 12:27:53</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.AddRowToMRVSSPTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>AddRowToMRVSSPTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var AddRowToMRVSSPTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
AddRowToMRVSSPTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

    generateTestStep: function() {

        if (!gs.nil(this.regressionObject.catalogItem)) {
            this.grATFStep.inputs['catalog_item'] = this.regressionObject.catalogItem;
        }
		if (!gs.nil(this.regressionObject.mrvs)) {
			var mrvsSysID = this.regressionObject.mrvs.split("IO:")[1];
			this.grATFStep.inputs['variable_set'] = mrvsSysID;
			gs.addInfoMessage( mrvsSysID);
		}
		
		this.grATFStep.notes = 'Variables Set Row added by the user during the recording';
		
        TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);

    },

    type: 'AddRowToMRVSSPTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-08-29 08:55:03</sys_created_on><sys_id>ef636e27db7ad0109e101461399619c5</sys_id><sys_mod_count>8</sys_mod_count><sys_name>AddRowToMRVSSPTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_ef636e27db7ad0109e101461399619c5</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:31</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description/><global>false</global><ignore_in_now_experience>false</ignore_in_now_experience><name>FormStateRegressionSnapshot</name><script><![CDATA[var regress = regress || {};

regress.ui16GlideForm = (function() {
    "use strict";

    //Class variables
    var primaryReferenceFields = [];
    var fieldState = new regress.FieldState();
    var populatedFieldsEncodedQuery;
    var defaultFieldsToValidate = [];

    // Extend Class BaseSnapshot
    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype = Object.create(regress.BaseSnapshot.FormStateSnapshot.prototype);
	// Update the constructor reference for spec conformance
	GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.constructor = GlideFormStateSnapshot;

   function GlideFormStateSnapshot() {
        regress.BaseSnapshot.FormStateSnapshot.call(this,g_form, g_user, g_sc_form);
        defaultFieldsToValidate = sessionDetails.existingRecordQueryFields.split(",");
        this.getSessionDetails();
    }

    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getMandatoryFields = function() {
        return fieldState.mandatory;
    };

    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getFieldState = function() {
        return fieldState;
    };


    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getPrimaryReferenceRecordFields = function() {
        return primaryReferenceFields;
    };

    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.snapshotFieldState = function(primaryReference) {

        var fieldElements = g_form.elements;

        for (var f in fieldElements) {
            if (fieldElements.hasOwnProperty(f)) {
                var fieldElement = fieldElements[f];
                getFieldState(fieldElement, primaryReference);
            }
        }

    };

     GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.logFieldState = function() {
        regress.log('Mandatory fields:' + fieldState.mandatory);
        regress.log('Read only fields:' + fieldState.readOnly);
        regress.log('Hidden fields:' + fieldState.hidden);
        regress.log('Optional fields:' + fieldState.optional);
        regress.log('Editable fields:' + fieldState.editable);
        regress.log('Visible fields:' + fieldState.visible);

    };

    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getDefaultFieldsToValidateAsEncQuery = function() {
        var encQueries = [];
        var encQry;
        for (var f = 0; f < defaultFieldsToValidate.length; f++) {
            var fieldName = defaultFieldsToValidate[f];
            regress.log('Processing ' + fieldName);
            var glideUIElement = g_form.getGlideUIElement(fieldName);
            if (glideUIElement) {
                var isVisible = g_form.isVisible(glideUIElement);
                if (isVisible) {
                    var value = g_form.getValue(fieldName);
                    encQueries.push(fieldName + '=' + value);
                }
            }

        }
        encQry = encQueries.join("^");
        regress.log(encQry);
        return;
    };

    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getAllChangedFieldsAsEncQry = function() {
        var allChangedFieldsAsEncQry = '';
        var changedFieldsQry = this.getChangedFieldsPart();

        if (changedFieldsQry != g_form.serializeTargetFields()) {
            // remove [tablename.]field part
            // incident.impact=1&incident.urgency=1&incident.priority=1 -> impact=1&urgency=1&priority=1
            var replaceTableNameRegEx = new RegExp(g_form.getTableName() + "\.", "g");
            allChangedFieldsAsEncQry = changedFieldsQry.replace(replaceTableNameRegEx, "");

            // replace & with ^ as to read like encoded query
            // impact=1&urgency=1&priority=1 -> impact=1^urgency=1^priority=1
            var replaceAmpersandRegEx = /\&/g;
            allChangedFieldsAsEncQry = allChangedFieldsAsEncQry.replace(replaceAmpersandRegEx, "^");

            // serialized string replaces spaces with + symbol. We need put the space back in
            // short_description=hello+my+old+friend -> short_description=hello my old friend
            allChangedFieldsAsEncQry = allChangedFieldsAsEncQry.replace(/\+/g, " ");
        }

        return allChangedFieldsAsEncQry;
    };



    // All fields changed are stored as a serialized query. 
    // We want to strip out only the part that has changed fields
    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getChangedFieldsPart = function() {

        // serializeChanged() example output 
        // e.g. &sys_target=incident&sys_uniqueValue=7d7ad766db86c0109e10146139961919&sys_row=0&sysparm_encoded_record=         &incident.impact=1&incident.urgency=1&incident.priority=1 
        var serializedChangedFields = g_form.serializeChanged();
        regress.log('serializedChangedFields:' + serializedChangedFields);

        // remove all junk variable details 
        // e.g. ni.ni.VE42e9ff70db3333001c4af53a299619c2TABLE=sys_user, ni.WATERMARK 
        var changedVariablesRegEx = new RegExp("&ni\.[^&]+", "g");
        serializedChangedFields = serializedChangedFields.replace(changedVariablesRegEx, "");
        regress.log('variables removed: ' + serializedChangedFields);

        // serializeTargetFields() example output
        // &sys_target=incident&sys_uniqueValue=7d7ad766db86c0109e10146139961919&sys_row=0&sysparm_encoded_record=
        var serializedTargetFields = g_form.serializeTargetFields();
        regress.log('serializeTargetFields:' + serializedTargetFields);

        // Remove serializeTargetFields part from serializeChanged and first ampersand
        // &incident.impact=1&incident.urgency=1&incident.priority=1 
        var changedFieldsOnly = serializedChangedFields.replace(serializedTargetFields + "&", '');
        regress.log('changedFieldsOnly:' + changedFieldsOnly);

        // Replace %20 with space
        var spaceReplacedFields = serializedChangedFields.replace(serializedTargetFields + "%20", ' ');

        return changedFieldsOnly;
    };

    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.snapshotPopulatedFieldsAndVariables = function() {

        if (g_form.getTableName() == "ni") {
            // Change variables in Service Catalog Form are not captured in modifiedFields
            this.snapshotPopulatatedVariables();
        } else {

            var modifiedFieldsAndVariables = Object.keys(g_form.modifiedFields); // ES2015 - This might fail in older browsers
            var fieldsWithChangedValues = [];
            var variablesWithChangedValues = [];
            var variablesEncQry = [];

            for (var i = 0; i < modifiedFieldsAndVariables.length; i++) {
                var fieldName = modifiedFieldsAndVariables[i];
                regress.log("Processing " + fieldName);

                if (g_form.modifiedFields[fieldName] == true) {

                    // Variables are prefixed with ni.VE
                    if (fieldName.indexOf("ni.VE") > -1) {
                        var variableNameMap = g_form.nameMap.find(function(element) {
                            return element.realName == fieldName;
                        }); // Not sure how to do this outside the function, not sure it matters

                        if (variableNameMap) {
                            var variableSysID = variableNameMap.questionID;
                            variablesWithChangedValues.push(variableSysID);
                            var query = "IO:" + variableSysID + "=" + g_form.getValue(fieldName);
                            variablesEncQry.push(query);
                        } else {
                            regress.log('Something went wrong finding the variable sys_id');
                        }

                    } else {
                        // Fields are prefixed with table name, e.g. incident.short_description
                        // TODO: Investigate using OOTB function for this instead
                        var fieldWithoutTablePrefix = fieldName.replace(tableName + ".", "");
                        fieldsWithChangedValues.push(fieldWithoutTablePrefix);
                    }
                }
            }

            regress.log("Fields changed: " + fieldsWithChangedValues);
            regress.log("Variables changed: " + variablesWithChangedValues);
            populatedFieldsEncodedQuery = createEncodedQueryFromFields(fieldsWithChangedValues);
            populatedVariablesEncodedQuery = variablesEncQry.join("^");

            regress.log("populatedVariablesEncodedQuery:" + populatedVariablesEncodedQuery);
        }
    };

    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.snapshotPopulatatedVariables = function() {

        var serializedChangedVariables = g_form.serializeChanged(); // In CatalogForm this gets all variables, not just those that are changed
        var serializedChangedVariablesArray = serializedChangedVariables.split("&");
        var changedVariablesArray = [];

        for (var i = 0; i < serializedChangedVariablesArray.length; i++) {

            var serializedVariable = serializedChangedVariablesArray[i];
            if (serializedVariable.startsWith("IO:")) {
                var splitVar = serializedVariable.split("=");
                var variableID = splitVar[0];
                var value = splitVar[1];
                var variableName = g_form.getAppliedFieldName(variableID);
                var isEditable = g_form.isEditableField(g_form.getSCUIElement(variableName),g_form.getControl(variableName));
                
                // We don't want to pick up variables with no value that are not visible or non-editable
                if (value != "" && value != null && value && isEditable) {
                    regress.log("Snapshot validate value for variable " + variableName + "=" + value);
                    changedVariablesArray.push(serializedVariable);                     
                } else {
                    regress.log("Ignoring variable " + variableName);
                }

            }

        }

        regress.log("Variables changed: " + changedVariablesArray);
        populatedVariablesEncodedQuery = changedVariablesArray.join("^");
        regress.log("populatedVariablesEncodedQuery:" + populatedVariablesEncodedQuery);
    };

    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getPopulatedVariablesAsEncQry = function() {
        return populatedVariablesEncodedQuery;
    };

    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getPopulatedFieldsAsEncQry = function() {
        return populatedFieldsEncodedQuery;
    };

    // This is how ServiceNow finds the UI Actions in the DOM in the 'Check UI Action Visibility' Test config
    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getVisibleUIActions = function() {

        var visibleUIActions = [];
        var queryString = "[gsft_id]";
        var uiActionElements = document.querySelectorAll(queryString);

        for (var i in uiActionElements) {
            var uiActionElement = uiActionElements[i];
            if (isElementVisible(uiActionElement)) {

                var sysId = uiActionElement.getAttribute("gsft_id");
                var type = uiActionElement.getAttribute("type");
                var actionName = uiActionElement.getAttribute("name");
                visibleUIActions.push(sysId);
                // Hidden elements are context menu items that aren't actually clicked
                // The elements that are actually clicked don't reference the ui action sys_id
                if (type == "hidden") {
                    // this will only work for server side ui actions
                    // as client side has href of ui action onclick and not the action name
                    // TODO: need seperate function for context menu, add event listener to clear clicked ui action value
                    var href = "gsftSubmit(gel('" + actionName + "'))";
                    regress.log('[REGRESS] Context item found for ' + actionName);
                    uiActionElement = this.getContextMenuElement(href);
                }

                if (uiActionElement != null) {
                    addUIActionListener(uiActionElement, sysId);
                } else {
                    regress.log('[REGRESS] Could not link action to element for ' + actionName);
                }

            }
        }

        return visibleUIActions;
    };

    // based on function of the same name in New York 'Click UI Action' step config
    GlideFormStateSnapshot.prototype.getContextMenuElement = function(href) {
        var contextMenuElements = window.contextMenus['context_1'] ? window.contextMenus['context_1'].children : null;
        if (!contextMenuElements)
            return null;

        var contextMenuElem = null;
        for (var i = 0; i < contextMenuElements.length; i += 1) {
            var contextMenuItem = contextMenuElements[i];
            if (!contextMenuItem)
                continue;

            if (contextMenuItem.getAttribute('href') === href) {
                contextMenuElem = contextMenuItem;
                regress.log('[REGRESS] Found UI action element for ' + contextMenuItem.getAttribute('href'));
                break;
            }
        }

            return contextMenuElem;
        };

        FormStateSnapshot.prototype.getSessionDetails = function(){
            var recordingSessionDetails;
            var recordingSessionDataJSON = this.g_user.getClientData("REGRESS_ATF_RECORDER");
            if (recordingSessionDataJSON != null) {
                recordingSessionDetails = JSON.parse(recordingSessionDataJSON);
            }
    
            return recordingSessionDetails;
        };

    return {
        GlideFormStateSnapshot: GlideFormStateSnapshot,
        type: 'ui16Form'
    };

    //Private Functions
    function addUIActionListener(uiActionElement, sysId) {
        uiActionElement.addEventListener('mousedown', function(e) {
            getActionClicked(sysId);
        });
    }

    function getActionClicked(sysId) {
        regress.log('[REGRESS] Button clicked/mouse down ' + sysId);
        regress.reg_form.setUIActionClicked(sysId);
    }

    function createEncodedQueryFromFields(fields) {

        var encodedQuery = '';
        var regressionQueryArray = [];
        for (var r in fields) {
            if (fields.hasOwnProperty(r)) {
                try {
                    var regFieldName = fields[r];
                    var qry = regFieldName + "=" + g_form.getValue(regFieldName);
                    regressionQueryArray.push(qry);

                } catch (e) {
                    // in case it cant get the field value for whatever reason
                    //regress.log("Excluding field " + regFieldName + ' reason:' + e);
                }
            }
        }

        encodedQuery = regressionQueryArray.join("^");

        return encodedQuery;
    }

    // This is how ServiceNow determine UI Action Visibility in ATF Test Config
    function isElementVisible(dom) {
      
    }

    function getFieldState(fieldElement, primaryReference) {

        
        var fieldTable = fieldElement.tableName;

        if (fieldName != '' && fieldName != null && fieldName != undefined) {
            if (fieldTable == tableName) {

                determineIfMandatoryField(fieldName);
                determineReadOnlyField(fieldName);
                determineIfVisibleField(fieldName);

                if (primaryReference != null && g_form.getValue(fieldName) == primaryReference) {
                    primaryReferenceFields.push(fieldName);
                }


                return true;
            }
        }

        return false;
    }

    function determineIfMandatoryField(fieldName) {

        var isMandatory = g_form.isMandatory(fieldName);
        if (isMandatory) {
            fieldState.mandatory.push(fieldName);
        } else {
            fieldState.optional.push(fieldName);
        }

        return isMandatory;
    }

    function determineReadOnlyField(fieldName) {

        var isReadOnly = g_form.isReadOnly(g_form.getElement(fieldName), g_form.getControl(fieldName));
        if (isReadOnly) {
            fieldState.readOnly.push(fieldName);
        } else {
            fieldState.editable.push(fieldName);
        }

        return isReadOnly;
    }

    function determineIfVisibleField(fieldName) {

		var glideUIElement = g_form.getGlideUIElement(fieldName);
        var control = g_form.getControl(fieldName);
		
        var isVisible = (!glideUIElement || !control) ? false : !!g_form.isVisible(glideUIElement, control);

        if (isVisible) {
            fieldState.visible.push(fieldName);
        } else {
			fieldState.hidden.push(fieldName);
        }

        return isVisible;
    }
    
})();]]></script><script_name/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-10-29 13:13:29</sys_created_on><sys_id>ca572d13db88a0109e101461399619b0</sys_id><sys_mod_count>79</sys_mod_count><sys_name>FormStateRegressionSnapshot</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_script_ca572d13db88a0109e101461399619b0</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>paul.morris</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2021-02-21 03:32:16</sys_updated_on><ui_type>10</ui_type><use_scoped_format>false</use_scoped_format></sys_ui_script></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_fix"><sys_script_fix action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><before>false</before><description>Do not use this script unless you are a Regress Developer. This is used to clean up the application of any unwanted files and reset all settings to default.</description><name>RegressBuildCleanupScript</name><record_for_rollback>true</record_for_rollback><script><![CDATA[(function cleanUp() {	
	//Delete any tests or steps sitting in Regress app scope
    var grATFTest = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_test');
    grATFTest.addEncodedQuery('sys_scope=86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f');
    grATFTest.deleteMultiple();

    var grATFStep = new GlideRecord('sys_atf_step');
    grATFStep.addEncodedQuery('sys_scope=86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f');
	grATFTest.deleteMultiple();

	//Remove all catalog variable sets
	var grCatalogVariableSet = new GlideRecord('io_set_item');
	grCatalogVariableSet.addEncodedQuery('variable_set=6df85e0ddb7f00109e101461399619f6');
	grCatalogVariableSet.deleteMultiple();

	//Remove all themes/scripts
	var grUIScriptTheme = new GlideRecord('m2m_sp_theme_js_include');
	grUIScriptTheme.addEncodedQuery('sp_js_include.display_name=RegressUI^ORsp_js_include.display_name=ServiceCatalogForm17^ORsp_js_include.display_name=ServiceCatalogFormSP');
	grUIScriptTheme.deleteMultiple();

	//Remove all unwanted app files
	//Delete guided setup status changes
	var grGuidedSetupContentStatus = new GlideRecord('gsw_status_of_content');
	grGuidedSetupContentStatus.addEncodedQuery('sys_scope=86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f');
	grGuidedSetupContentStatus.deleteMultiple();

	var grGuidedSetupChangeLogs = new GlideRecord('gsw_change_log');
	grGuidedSetupChangeLogs.addEncodedQuery('sys_scope=86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f');
	grGuidedSetupChangeLogs.deleteMultiple();

	//Remove unwanted deleted app files
	var grUnwantedAppFiles = new GlideRecord('sys_metadata');
	grUnwantedAppFiles.addEncodedQuery('sys_scope=86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f^sys_class_name=sys_metadata_delete^sys_update_nameSTARTSWITHgsw_status_of_content^ORsys_update_nameSTARTSWITHgsw_change_logt^ORsys_update_nameSTARTSWITHsys_atf_step^ORsys_update_nameSTARTSWITHsys_atf_test');
	grUnwantedAppFiles.deleteMultiple();

	//Reset all settings to default
	var regressSystemPropertyHelper = new RegressSystemPropertyHelper();
    regressSystemPropertyHelper.resetPropertiesToDefault();
	
})();]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_fix</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sn-nerd</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2023-02-04 04:21:00</sys_created_on><sys_id>a3c17ba147bc2110cef68a5f746d4332</sys_id><sys_mod_count>14</sys_mod_count><sys_name>RegressBuildCleanupScript</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_fix_a3c17ba147bc2110cef68a5f746d4332</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-24 13:00:19</sys_updated_on><unloadable>true</unloadable></sys_script_fix></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_include_4b6061a4dbb10010f0a2f282399619b1
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.VisibleUIActionTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>VisibleUIActionTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var VisibleUIActionTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
VisibleUIActionTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

	generateTestStep: function() {

		if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotVisibleUIActions() || RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingVisibleUIActions()) {
			if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotVisibleUIActions()) {
				this.grATFStep.inputs['not_visible'] = this.getPossibleNotVisibleUIActions();
				this.grATFStep.notes = "The UI Actions visible during and all UI actions that were not visible";
			} 
			if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingVisibleUIActions()) {
				this.grATFStep.inputs['visible'] = this.regressionObject.visibleUIActions;
				if (!RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingNotVisibleUIActions())
					this.grATFStep.notes = "The UI Actions visible during recording.";
			}

			TestStepGenerator.prototype.generateTestStep.call(this);

		} else {
			// Delete test step if UI action visibility is not being captured
			this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();
		}

	},
	
	getPossibleNotVisibleUIActions: function() {
		var notVisibleUIActions = [];
		// The query string returned from getFormUIAction (OOTB, used by ATF) excludes inactive
		var encQry = getFormUIAction(this.regressionObject.tableName);
		if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCapturingInactiveUIActions()) {
			// we want to include active=false to be able to perform exhaustive regression, so remove existing active=true returned from getFormUIAction
			encQry.replace("^active=true", "");
		}
		
		var ignoreUIActionsQry = "^sys_id!=sysverb_post_update^sys_id!=sysverb_query"; // these are UI actions for 'Search' and 'Update' that we don't want
		encQry = encQry + "^sys_idNOT IN" + this.regressionObject.visibleUIActions + ignoreUIActionsQry;
		
		var grUIActions = new GlideRecord('sys_ui_action');
		grUIActions.addEncodedQuery(encQry);
		grUIActions.setLimit(150);
		grUIActions.query();
		
		while (grUIActions.next()) {
			// Have not been able to work out how to determine visibility for client actions in form context menu
			// There is no reference to the UI action sys_id in the DOM 
			if (!(grUIActions.getValue('client') == true && grUIActions.getValue('form_context_menu') == true)) {
				notVisibleUIActions.push(grUIActions.getUniqueValue());
			}
		}
		
		return notVisibleUIActions.join(",");
	},
	
    type: 'VisibleUIActionTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-12-15 07:06:34</sys_created_on><sys_id>4b6061a4dbb10010f0a2f282399619b1</sys_id><sys_mod_count>23</sys_mod_count><sys_name>VisibleUIActionTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_4b6061a4dbb10010f0a2f282399619b1</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>snnerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2022-05-02 09:27:28</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.FieldValuesValidationTestStepGenerator</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>FieldValuesValidationTestStepGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var FieldValuesValidationTestStepGenerator = Class.create();
FieldValuesValidationTestStepGenerator.prototype = Object.extendsObject(TestStepGenerator, {

	generateTestStep: function() {
		// validateFieldValues

		var hasChangedFieldValues =  !gs.nil(this.regressionObject.changedFieldValues);
		var hasAdditionalCapturedFields = !gs.nil(this.regressionObject.validateFieldValues);
		var noFieldValuesCaptured = !hasChangedFieldValues && !hasAdditionalCapturedFields;
		var validateFieldValuesArray = [];
		var notes = 'Check all field values that were changed on the form, including by scripts, and validate field values selected by user via the context menu';;

		if (noFieldValuesCaptured) {
			this.grATFStep.deleteRecord();
			return;
		} 
		
		if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCaptureFieldsChangedByScriptEnabled() && hasChangedFieldValues) {
			validateFieldValuesArray.push(this.regressionObject.changedFieldValues);
		}
		if (hasAdditionalCapturedFields)  {
			validateFieldValuesArray.push(this.regressionObject.validateFieldValues);
		}

		var condition = validateFieldValuesArray.join("^");

		this.generateFieldValuesValidationTest(condition, notes);

	},
	
	generateFieldValuesValidationTest: function(conditions, notes)  {
		if (RegressATFRecordSessionv2.isCreateUserWhenImpersonating()) {
			conditions = this.replaceCurrentUserSysIDWithStepRef(conditions);
		} 
		
		this.grATFStep.notes = notes;
		this.setContextualValueVariable('conditions',conditions);
        
	},

    type: 'FieldValuesValidationTestStepGenerator'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-09-15 04:04:32</sys_created_on><sys_id>d11e80d3db7333001c4af53a29961992</sys_id><sys_mod_count>36</sys_mod_count><sys_name>FieldValuesValidationTestStepGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_d11e80d3db7333001c4af53a29961992</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-21 11:22:30</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>
