<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description/><global>false</global><ignore_in_now_experience>false</ignore_in_now_experience><name>GlideFormUI16</name><script><![CDATA[regress.GlideFormUI16 = (function() {
    "use strict";

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype = Object.create(regress.ServiceCatalogForm17.FormSnapshot.prototype);
    GlideFormSnapshot.constructor = GlideFormSnapshot;

    function GlideFormSnapshot() {
        regress.ServiceCatalogForm17.FormSnapshot.call(this);
        regress.common.log('GlideFormSnapshot()');
        this.variableStateChecker = new regress.VariableStateChecker.VariableStateChecker(regress.common.gSCForm);
        this.fieldStateChecker = new regress.FieldStateChecker.FieldStateChecker();
        this.uiActionClicked = null;
        this.validateFields = [];
        this.recordFormState.fieldState = {};
        this.recordFormState.populatedFieldValues = ''; // manually
        this.recordFormState.changedFieldValues = ''; // by script
		this.recordFormState.validateFieldValues = ''; //using context menu 'capture field value'
        this.recordFormState.visibleUIActions = '';
        this.recordFormState.uiAction = '';
        this.recordFormState.tableName = regress.common.gForm.getTableName();
        this.recordFormState.sysID = regress.common.gForm.getUniqueValue();;
        this.recordFormState.display = regress.common.gForm.getDisplayValue();
        this.recordFormState.isNewRecord = regress.common.gForm.isNewRecord();
        this.recordFormState.viewName = regress.common.gForm.getViewName();
        if (typeof regress.common.gSCForm != 'undefined') {
            this.recordFormState.catalogItem = regress.common.gSCForm.getUniqueValue();
        }
        this.recordFormState.visibleUIActions = this.getVisibleUIActions();
        this.recordFormState.existingRecordQuery = this.createExistingRecordEncodedQuery();

    }

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.canSnapshotField = function(fieldName) {
        return !this.validateFields.includes(fieldName);
    };

	GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.snapshotField = function(fieldName) {
        if (this.canSnapshotField(fieldName)) {
            this.validateFields.push(fieldName);
            regress.common.gForm.addDecoration(fieldName, 'icon-add', 'Recorded Field', 'color-blue');
            regress.common.gForm.addInfoMessage("The value of field'" +fieldName+"' when the form is saved will be added to a 'Validate Field Value' Test Step.");
        }
	};

	GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.snapshotFieldAdditionalFields = function() {
        var additionalFieldQueries = [];
        this.validateFields.forEach(function doThing(fieldName) {
            var value = regress.common.gForm.getValue(fieldName);
            var qry = fieldName + "=" + value;
            additionalFieldQueries.push(qry);
        });
        var validateAdditionalFieldValues = additionalFieldQueries.join("^");
        console.log(validateAdditionalFieldValues);

        return validateAdditionalFieldValues;
	};

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.takeSnapshot = function() {
        regress.ServiceCatalogForm17.FormSnapshot.prototype.takeSnapshot.call(this);
        // Need a new object as existing contains init mandatory variables
        this.fieldStateChecker = new regress.FieldStateChecker.FieldStateChecker(); 
        this.recordFormState.fieldState = this.snapshotFieldState();
        this.recordFormState.changedFieldValues = this.getAllChangedFieldsAsEncQry();
        this.recordFormState.validateFieldValues = this.snapshotFieldAdditionalFields();

        return  this.recordFormState;
    };

    // Get all mandatory fields and turn into an encoded query to use for record likeness in the ATF Test
    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.createExistingRecordEncodedQuery = function() {
        var existingRecordQuery;
        var fieldState = this.snapshotFieldState();
        var mandatoryFields = fieldState.mandatory;
        existingRecordQuery = this.determineExistingRecordQuery(mandatoryFields);
        regress.common.log('Initially mandatory fields: ' + mandatoryFields);

        return existingRecordQuery;
    };   

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.determineExistingRecordQuery = function(mandatoryFields) {
        var encodedQuery = '';
        var regressionQueryArray = [];
        var fieldName, qry;

        for (var i = 0; i < mandatoryFields.length; i++) {
            fieldName = mandatoryFields[i];
            var value = regress.common.gForm.getValue(fieldName);

            // A form can load with mandatory fields that are not populated!
            // We only care about mandatory fields that are populated
            if (value != "") {
                regress.common.log("Field " + fieldName + " used for existing record query");
                regress.common.log("value: " + value);
                if (value == "true") {
                    //Mandatory True/false fields can't be empty, only true
                    qry = fieldName + "=true";
                } else {
                    qry = fieldName + "!="; // is not
                }
                regressionQueryArray.push(qry);
            }

        }

        encodedQuery = regressionQueryArray.join("^");
 
        return encodedQuery;
    };   



    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.setUIActionClicked = function(uiActionSysID) {
        this.recordFormState.uiAction = uiActionSysID;
        regress.common.log('UI Action found through event handler, found:' + uiActionSysID);
    };

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.snapshotFieldState = function() {
        var fieldElements = regress.common.gForm.elements;
        for (var f in fieldElements) {
            if (fieldElements.hasOwnProperty(f)) {
                var fieldElement = fieldElements[f];
                var fieldName = fieldElement.fieldName;
                var fieldTable = fieldElement.tableName;
                if (fieldName != '' && fieldName != null && fieldName != undefined) {
                    // Ensure field is not a dot walked field, you can't select those in ATF
                    if (fieldTable == this.recordFormState.tableName) {
                        this.fieldStateChecker.getState(fieldName, fieldName);
                    } else {
                        regress.common.log('Field ' + fieldName + ' was ignored as it does not belong to table name ' + this.recordFormState.tableName);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        return this.fieldStateChecker.getAllStates();
    };

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.snapshotPopulatatedData = function() {

        regress.common.log('GlideForm snapshotPopulatatedData');
        var modifiedFieldsAndVariables = Object.keys(regress.common.gForm.modifiedFields); // ES2015 - This might fail in older browsers
        var fieldsWithChangedValues = [];
        var variablesWithChangedValues = [];
        var variablesEncQry = [];

        for (var i = 0; i < modifiedFieldsAndVariables.length; i++) {
            var fieldName = modifiedFieldsAndVariables[i];

            if (regress.common.gForm.modifiedFields[fieldName] == true) {

                // Variables are prefixed with ni.VE
                if (fieldName.indexOf("ni.VE") > -1) {
                    var variableNameMap = regress.common.gForm.nameMap.find(function(element) {
                        return element.realName == fieldName;
                    }); // Not sure how to do this outside the function, not sure it matters

                    if (variableNameMap) {
                        var variableSysID = variableNameMap.questionID;
                        variablesWithChangedValues.push(variableSysID);
                        var query = "IO:" + variableSysID + "=" + regress.common.gForm.getValue(fieldName);
                        variablesEncQry.push(query);
                    } else {
                        regress.common.log('Something went wrong finding the variable sys_id');
                    }

                } else {
                    // Fields are prefixed with table name, e.g. incident.short_description
                    // TODO: Investigate using OOTB function for this instead

                    var fieldWithoutTablePrefix = fieldName.replace(this.recordFormState.tableName + ".", "");
                    var control = regress.common.gForm.getControl(fieldWithoutTablePrefix);
                    var ge = regress.common.gForm.getGlideUIElement(fieldWithoutTablePrefix);
                    // Scoped forms included fields populated by script, which could be Read Only
                    if (!regress.common.gForm.isReadOnly(ge,control)) {
                        fieldsWithChangedValues.push(fieldWithoutTablePrefix);
                    } else {
                        regress.common.log('Field ' + fieldWithoutTablePrefix + " ignored because it is read only" );
                    }
                }
            }
            
            this.recordFormState.populatedFieldValues = this.createEncodedQueryFromFields(fieldsWithChangedValues);
            this.recordFormState.populatedVariableValues = variablesEncQry.join("^");

        }
    };

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.createEncodedQueryFromFields = function(fields) {
        var encodedQuery = '';
        var regressionQueryArray = [];
        for (var r in fields) {
            if (fields.hasOwnProperty(r)) {
                try {
                    var regFieldName = fields[r];
                    var qry = regFieldName + "=" + regress.common.gForm.getValue(regFieldName);
                    regressionQueryArray.push(qry);

                } catch (e) {
                    // in case it cant get the field value for whatever reason
                    //regress.log("Excluding field " + regFieldName + ' reason:' + e);
                }
            }
        }

        encodedQuery = regressionQueryArray.join("^");

        return encodedQuery;
    };

    // This is how ServiceNow finds the UI Actions in the DOM in the 'Check UI Action Visibility' Test config
    // Does not get client UI actions in the context menu
    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.getVisibleUIActions = function() {

        var visibleUIActions = [];
        var queryString = "[gsft_id]";
        var uiActionElements = document.querySelectorAll(queryString);

        for (var i in uiActionElements) {
            var uiActionElement = uiActionElements[i];
            if (this.isElementVisible(uiActionElement)) {

                var sysId = uiActionElement.getAttribute("gsft_id");
                var type = uiActionElement.getAttribute("type");
                var actionName = uiActionElement.getAttribute("name");
                visibleUIActions.push(sysId);
                // Hidden elements are context menu items that aren't actually clicked
                // The elements that are actually clicked don't reference the ui action sys_id
                if (type == "hidden") {
                    // this will only work for server side ui actions
                    // as client side has href of ui action onclick and not the action name
                    var href = "gsftSubmit(gel('" + actionName + "'))";
                    uiActionElement = this.getContextMenuElement(href);
                }

                if (uiActionElement != null) {
                    // Add an event listener to each UI action so we can trace it and determine which was selected
                    this.addUIActionListener(uiActionElement, sysId);
                } else {
                    regress.common.log('Could not link action to element for ' + actionName);
                }

            }
        }

        return visibleUIActions;
    };

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.addUIActionListener = function(uiActionElement, sysId) {
        var regicide = this;
        uiActionElement.addEventListener('mousedown', function(e) {
            regress.common.log('Button clicked/mouse down for UI action with sys_id of ' + sysId);
            jslog(regicide.recordFormState);
            regicide.recordFormState.uiAction = sysId;

        });
    };


    // based on function of the same name in New York 'Click UI Action' step config
    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.getContextMenuElement = function(href) {
        var contextMenuElements = window.contextMenus['context_1'] ? window.contextMenus['context_1'].children : null;
        if (!contextMenuElements)
            return null;

        var contextMenuElem = null;
        for (var i = 0; i < contextMenuElements.length; i += 1) {
            var contextMenuItem = contextMenuElements[i];
            if (!contextMenuItem)
                continue;

            if (contextMenuItem.getAttribute('href') === href) {
                contextMenuElem = contextMenuItem;
                break;
            }
        }

            return contextMenuElem;
        };

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.getContextElements = function() {
        var contextMenuElements = window.contextMenus['context_1'] ? window.contextMenus['context_1'].children : null;
        
        if (!contextMenuElements)
            return null;

        var contextMenuElem;

        for (var i = 0; i < contextMenuElements.length; i += 1) {
            var contextMenuItem = contextMenuElements[i];
            if (!contextMenuItem)
                continue;

            if (contextMenuItem.getAttribute('href') === actionOnclick) {
                contextMenuElem = contextMenuItem;
                break;
            }
        }

        return contextMenuElem;
    },

    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.isElementVisible = function(dom) {
        var answer = false;
        if (typeof dom != "function") {
            try {
                answer = !dom.hidden && dom.style.visibility != 'hidden';
            } catch (e) {
                regress.common.log('element ' + dom + ' visibility cannot be determined');
            }
        }

        return answer;
    };


    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.getAllChangedFieldsAsEncQry = function() {
        var allChangedFieldsAsEncQry = '';
        var changedFieldsQry = this.getChangedFieldsPart();

        if (changedFieldsQry != regress.common.gForm.serializeTargetFields()) {
            // remove [tablename.]field part
            // incident.impact=1&incident.urgency=1&incident.priority=1 -> impact=1&urgency=1&priority=1
            var replaceTableNameRegEx = new RegExp(g_form.getTableName() + "\.", "g");
            allChangedFieldsAsEncQry = changedFieldsQry.replace(replaceTableNameRegEx, "");

            // replace & with ^ as to read like encoded query
            // impact=1&urgency=1&priority=1 -> impact=1^urgency=1^priority=1
            var replaceAmpersandRegEx = /\&/g;
            allChangedFieldsAsEncQry = allChangedFieldsAsEncQry.replace(replaceAmpersandRegEx, "^");

            // serialized string replaces spaces with + symbol. We need put the space back in
            // short_description=hello+my+old+friend -> short_description=hello my old friend
            allChangedFieldsAsEncQry = allChangedFieldsAsEncQry.replace(/\+/g, " ");
        }

        regress.common.log('Changed fields enc qry: ' + allChangedFieldsAsEncQry);

        return allChangedFieldsAsEncQry;
    };



    // All fields changed are stored as a serialized query. 
    // We want to strip out only the part that has changed fields
    GlideFormSnapshot.prototype.getChangedFieldsPart = function() {

        // serializeChanged() example output 
        // e.g. &sys_target=incident&sys_uniqueValue=7d7ad766db86c0109e10146139961919&sys_row=0&sysparm_encoded_record=         &incident.impact=1&incident.urgency=1&incident.priority=1 
        var serializedChangedFields = regress.common.gForm.serializeChanged();

        // remove all junk variable details 
        // e.g. ni.ni.VE42e9ff70db3333001c4af53a299619c2TABLE=sys_user, ni.WATERMARK 
        var changedVariablesRegEx = new RegExp("&ni\.[^&]+", "g");
        serializedChangedFields = serializedChangedFields.replace(changedVariablesRegEx, "");

        // serializeTargetFields() example output
        // &sys_target=incident&sys_uniqueValue=7d7ad766db86c0109e10146139961919&sys_row=0&sysparm_encoded_record=
        var serializedTargetFields = regress.common.gForm.serializeTargetFields();

        // Remove serializeTargetFields part from serializeChanged and first ampersand
        // &incident.impact=1&incident.urgency=1&incident.priority=1 
        var changedFieldsOnly = serializedChangedFields.replace(serializedTargetFields + "&", '');


        // Decode URI characters (e.g. %20 = black space)
        var decodedURI = decodeURIComponent(changedFieldsOnly);
        regress.common.log('Change Fields part:' + decodedURI);

        return decodedURI;
    };


    return {
        GlideFormSnapshot: GlideFormSnapshot,
        type: 'GlideFormUI16'
    };



})();]]></script><script_name/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>paul.morris</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-02-14 04:29:12</sys_created_on><sys_id>5d4bb3f52f5eac105a445e492799b616</sys_id><sys_mod_count>112</sys_mod_count><sys_name>GlideFormUI16</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder" source="86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Regress Premium - ATF Recorder">86935f2adbc233001c4af53a2996191f</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_script_5d4bb3f52f5eac105a445e492799b616</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sn-nerd</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2023-02-25 05:27:18</sys_updated_on><ui_type>0</ui_type><use_scoped_format>false</use_scoped_format></sys_ui_script></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="catalog_ui_policy"><catalog_ui_policy action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>false</active><applies_catalog>true</applies_catalog><applies_req_item>false</applies_req_item><applies_sc_task>false</applies_sc_task><applies_target_record>false</applies_target_record><applies_to>item</applies_to><catalog_conditions>IO:a9432f8b2f8320105a445e492799b6c9!=true^EQ</catalog_conditions><catalog_item display_value="Regress Properties">e194ce26db42c0109e10146139961954</catalog_item><conditions/><description/><global>true</global><inherit>false</inherit><isolate_script>true</isolate_script><model_id/><model_table/><on_load>true</on_load><order>100</order><reverse_if_false>true</reverse_if_false><run_scripts>false</run_scripts><script_false><![CDATA[function onCondition() {
